#: data/units/Bowman.cfg:3
msgid "Bowman"
msgstr "弓箭手"

#: data/units/Bowman.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The use of archery in shooting something other than game was seen from its "
"inception, and archers have been indispensable in warfare since time "
"immemorial. Usually of humble origins, hailing from the peasantry or the odd "
"woodsman, bowmen have reasonable prowess with both a bow and a short sword, "
"and are very common on the battlefield."
msgstr ""
"至古以来，这些善于射箭的单位一直是战斗中不可或缺的单位。通常来至于劳动阶层，"
"多数是农民和古怪的发木工，弓箭手非常善于使用弓和短剑，在战斗中是很有用的。"

#: data/units/Cavalier.cfg:3
msgid "Cavalier"
msgstr "骑兵"

#: data/units/Cavalier.cfg:38
msgid ""
"A triumphant sight on the battlefield, cavaliers are masters at the use of "
"both sword and crossbow from horseback. Their facility with ranged weapons "
"allows them to strike at many a foe with impunity, and their mettle has "
"turned the tide of some of the greatest battles in known history."
msgstr ""
"得益于足够的战斗经验，骑兵是马背上的剑术和弩弓使用大师。他们善于运用远程武"
"器，使得远处的敌人被攻击多次而不受惩罚，他们在战场上勇气非凡的表现在以知的历"
"史中处处皆是。"

#: data/units/Cavalier.cfg:77 data/units/Death_Knight.cfg:61
#: data/units/Dragoon.cfg:81 data/units/Duelist.cfg:94
#: data/units/General.cfg:70 data/units/Grand_Marshal.cfg:66
#: data/units/Lieutenant.cfg:54 data/units/Master_at_Arms.cfg:59
#: data/units/Orcish_Crossbowman.cfg:47 data/units/Orcish_Crossbowman.cfg:76
#: data/units/Orcish_Slurbow.cfg:48 data/units/Orcish_Slurbow.cfg:77
#: data/units/Sergeant.cfg:52
msgid "crossbow"
msgstr "弩弓"

#: data/units/Cavalryman.cfg:3
msgid "Cavalryman"
msgstr "骑兵"

#: data/units/Cavalryman.cfg:40
msgid ""
"Cavalrymen are distinguished from horsemen by their tactics and equipment. A "
"cavalryman wears heavier armor, and carries a sword and shield, rather than "
"a lance. Their tactics do not include charging, but instead maneuvers like "
"hit and run slashes with their sword, using both horse and rider as an "
"effective tool of melee.\n"
"\n"
"Cavalrymen are very useful for taking and holding positions on open ground, "
"for screening friendly soldiers, and also for scoutwork."
msgstr ""
"骑兵以他们在马背上独特的战斗方式和装备而闻名。骑兵装备重甲和剑盾，或者长矛。"
"他们的战术不包括冲锋，却用剑来打击和挥砍而代替，使用马和自己来作为有效的近战"
"攻击手段。\n"
"\n"
"骑兵通常用来查看和占领空旷地带的有力地形，用于查看友好士兵和侦察工作。"

#: data/units/Cave_Spider.cfg:3
msgid "Giant Spider"
msgstr "巨蜘蛛"

#: data/units/Cave_Spider.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Giant Spiders are said to roam the depths of Knalga, devouring many victims. "
"They can bite at close range, thereby poisoning their enemies, and also can "
"attack with a web at long range, slowing their foes down."
msgstr ""
"巨蜘蛛通常生活在Knalga的深处，以许多受害者为事。它们能用毒素在近战中打击对"
"手，也能在远处用蜘蛛网来减慢对手的速度。"

#: data/units/Cave_Spider.cfg:56
msgid "web"
msgstr "蜘蛛网"

#: data/units/Cave_Spider.cfg:74 data/units/Elvish_Druid.cfg:57
#: data/units/Elvish_Enchantress.cfg:83 data/units/Elvish_Shaman.cfg:59
#: data/units/Elvish_Shyde.cfg:67 data/units/Elvish_Sorceress.cfg:83
#: data/units/Elvish_Sylph.cfg:62 data/units/Goblin_Pillager.cfg:59
#: data/units/Merman_Entangler.cfg:34 data/units/Merman_Netcaster.cfg:33
msgid "slow"
msgstr "减速"

#: data/units/Cuttle_Fish.cfg:3
msgid "Cuttle Fish"
msgstr "章鱼人"

#: data/units/Cuttle_Fish.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Cuttle Fish are gigantic creatures of the seas. They can grab their "
"opponents with strong tentacles, or spit a poisonous black ink from a "
"distance. The best way to survive an encounter with these monsters is to "
"remain ashore."
msgstr ""
"章鱼人是海洋中巨大的生物。他们能用巨大的触须来打击对手，或在一定距离内射出有"
"毒的墨汁。要想在这些生物手里逃生，最好的办法是呆在岸上。"

#: data/units/Cuttle_Fish.cfg:39 data/units/Tentacle.cfg:62
msgid "tentacle"
msgstr "触须"

#: data/units/Cuttle_Fish.cfg:42
#, fuzzy
msgid "swarm"
msgstr "猛击"

#: data/units/Cuttle_Fish.cfg:76
msgid "ink"
msgstr "墨汁"

#: data/units/Dark_Adept.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Adept"
msgstr "黑暗狂热者"

#: data/units/Dark_Adept.cfg:28
msgid ""
"To attract any practitioners, the lure of black magic must be a great prize "
"indeed, for anyone caught practicing the art in the civilized world is "
"subject to a death sentence. And yet there are those who pursue this art, "
"for the prize offered is nothing less than immortality. Hidden away in "
"secret cults, or initiated into the dark orders of the underworld, the "
"training which these fanatics must endure often drives them to exhaustion "
"and enfeeblement.\n"
"\n"
"In such condition, their only weapon is the craft they have so committed "
"themselves to learning.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: The attacks of a dark adept are magical, and always have a "
"high chance of hitting an opponent."
msgstr ""
"为了攻击对手，使用黑暗魔法的代价是巨大的，任何在这个文明世界里想寻找黑暗力量"
"的最好途径就是研究死亡审判。最终所花的代价就是，除了不朽你将一无所有。隐秘的"
"巫术仪式，或受雇于地下世界，这些狂热的学习和魔法使用会让这些人变得虚弱无"
"力。\n"
"\n"
"通常，他们唯一的武器是自己通过学习而制造的。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：黑暗狂热者的攻击属于魔法攻击，同常对对手有很高的击中比率。"

#: data/units/Dark_Adept.cfg:31
#, fuzzy
msgid "shadow wave"
msgstr "猛推"

#: data/units/Dark_Adept.cfg:94
msgid "female^Dark Adept"
msgstr "女性黑暗狂热者"

#: data/units/Dark_Sorcerer.cfg:3
msgid "Dark Sorcerer"
msgstr "黑暗术士"

#: data/units/Dark_Sorcerer.cfg:28
msgid ""
"The dread inspired by black magic comes chiefly from how little is known "
"about it, to the common man. If immortality is truly what it grants, then "
"the transformation to lichdom would seem something to be achieved as soon as "
"possible, lest disease or infirmity claim the mage. Yet, on occasion, a dark "
"sorcerer has been seen who was quite aged, and yet clearly powerful enough "
"to rival a lich.\n"
"\n"
"One can only speculate why such a person would delay, or forgo that path "
"entirely. It is surmised that either lichdom falls short of the true "
"immortality it is claimed to be, or that there is a terrible and unspoken "
"price for becoming one.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the ranged attacks of a dark sorcerer are magical, and always "
"have a high chance of hitting an opponent. The staff of a dark sorcerer is "
"marked with the plague, and any foe struck down by it will rise again in "
"unlife."
msgstr ""
"他们主要的邪恶魔法攻击被世人知之甚少。如果不朽真的存在，则变为巫妖是他们一直"
"所向往的，免得疾病和衰弱宽饶这些魔法师。黑暗术士常常看上去很老，并有足够的能"
"量成为巫妖。\n"
"\n"
"仅剩的问题是为什么一个人要耽搁，或完全放弃那条路。推测是缺少变为不朽巫妖的条"
"件或是需要付出无数的代价。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：黑暗术士的远程攻击是魔法攻击，并对对手有很高的击中比率。黑暗术士的"
"武器是瘟疫，并且对手死后为他的不死部下。"

#: data/units/Dark_Sorcerer.cfg:37 data/units/Soulless.cfg:54
msgid "plague(Walking Corpse)"
msgstr "瘟疫(僵尸)"

#: data/units/Dark_Sorcerer.cfg:57 data/units/Necromancer.cfg:48
msgid "chill wave"
msgstr "冷冻波"

#: data/units/Death_Knight.cfg:3
msgid "Death Knight"
msgstr "死亡骑士"

#: data/units/Death_Knight.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Tales are told of the mightiest warriors and generals, who, cursed with hate "
"and a sense of betrayal, came back to this world as Death Knights. Wielding "
"the same weapons as they did before, they command the Undead in their quest "
"for revenge."
msgstr ""
"这些强大的战士和将军，被憎恨诅咒或有着强大的怨念，死后作为死亡骑士重新来到这"
"个世界。使用死前同样的武器，他们指挥不死单位来复仇。"

#: data/units/Death_Knight.cfg:42 data/units/Dwarvish_Lord.cfg:34
#: data/units/Dwarvish_Steelclad.cfg:33
msgid "battle axe"
msgstr "战斧"

#: data/units/Deathblade.cfg:3
msgid "Deathblade"
msgstr "死亡剑士"

#: data/units/Deathblade.cfg:26
msgid ""
"In life, the abominations known as 'Deathblades' were masters of combat, "
"soldiers who were both lithe and deadly. Their new masters will often "
"recognize this, and try to take advantage of it by outfitting them to match "
"the skills they once had. Though frail, these monsters are much faster than "
"the rest of their kind, both on foot and with their blades."
msgstr ""
"在生命中，‘死亡剑士’这战斗大师是被人所深恶痛绝的，这些士兵虽然软弱但也是致命"
"的。他们的新主人意识到这一点，试着配置他们死前拥有的技能来占据有利地位。虽然"
"虚弱，这些怪兽也比其他休眠的同类要快，无论是步伐或剑术上。"

#: data/units/Direwolf_Rider.cfg:3
msgid "Direwolf Rider"
msgstr "邪恶狼骑士"

#: data/units/Direwolf_Rider.cfg:35
msgid ""
"'Dire wolves' differ from the garden variety only in size and color. They "
"typically stand taller than a horse at the shoulder, and have an appetite to "
"match. Only a madman would willingly encounter them; the goblins, at great "
"cost to themselves, have managed to tame them, if such can be said.\n"
"\n"
"The claws of a wolf are not generally regarded as being the more dangerous "
"parts, but on a beast this large, they are thicker and longer than iron "
"nails. Their riders smear a poison on the front set, not unlike that used by "
"the orcish assassins, making a swipe from these beasts' paws into a most "
"deadly stroke.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: anyone struck by a direwolf's claws will be poisoned, and "
"victims of this poison will continually take damage until they can be cured "
"in town or by a healer."
msgstr ""
"‘邪恶狼’和普通的区别仅仅在于大小和颜色。他们站起来时肩膀与马背平齐。并有特殊"
"的食物喜好。只有疯子才愿意和他们遭遇：就想传说中那样，只有地精可以驯服他们，"
"当然得花些代价。\n"
"\n"
"狼爪常常不被认为是最危险的部分，但这些又长又厚的巨爪能够穿过铁甲。这些骑手会"
"在前面装置上涂毒，且不同于兽人暗杀者，这些强有力的爪会造成致命攻击。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：任何人被邪恶狼爪击中后都会中毒，并持续掉血直到被治愈或回到村庄。"

#: data/units/Dragoon.cfg:3
msgid "Dragoon"
msgstr "龙骑士"

#: data/units/Dragoon.cfg:37
msgid ""
"The more talented cavalrymen in the armies of Wesnoth are trained in the use "
"of the crossbow, and outfitted with much more powerful steeds. Well-armored, "
"and skilled in the use of their swords, these soldiers can drive forward and "
"hold the ground they take. Their mobility and resilience make them of great "
"value on the battlefield."
msgstr ""
"在韦诺世界军队里越多善于用弩，并装备强力武器和有效装甲，善于用剑的骑士，能迅"
"速占领战略重要地形。他们的机动性和反弹攻击会使得在战场中具有极大价值。"

#: data/units/Drake_Blademaster.cfg:4
msgid "Drake Blademaster"
msgstr "大师级龙剑士"

#: data/units/Drake_Blademaster.cfg:33
msgid ""
"The drakes who master the use of a sword are sworn into a special order. The "
"mark of this is the black and white warpaint they display in battle."
msgstr ""
"那些非常善于用剑的龙剑士会被赋予其它的人物。在战争中会由白色和黑色来描绘，以"
"示区别。"

#: data/units/Drake_Burner.cfg:3
msgid "Drake Burner"
msgstr "喷火龙战士"

#: data/units/Drake_Burner.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Drake Burners are the few and the proud, who have inherited most truly the "
"strengths of their remote ancestors, especially the ability to breathe fire. "
"This, coupled with their sheer size and clawed hands makes for a dangerous "
"foe in combat."
msgstr ""
"喷火龙战士少而自大，他们由祖先遗传下强大的力量，特别是吐火的能力。那对够大和"
"有爪的双手使得他们成对战斗中危险的对手。"

#: data/units/Drake_Clasher.cfg:3
msgid "Drake Clasher"
msgstr "冲刺龙战士"

#: data/units/Drake_Clasher.cfg:26
msgid ""
"A Drake Clasher is incapable of both flight and fire-breathing, and most "
"assume their relegation to melee combat is because of disability - an "
"attempt to garner use from what otherwise would be a liability. It is "
"possible that they have some mild deficiency in those skills, but those who "
"support this theory have failed to consider how uniquely well-suited they "
"are to combat a fellow drake.\n"
"\n"
"They are, in fact, the Judicators of the Drake Hierarchy, and though their "
"armament is now largely ceremonial, it is none the less effective. In their "
"encounters with lesser races, they discovered that their natural size and "
"strength were themselves powerful weapons, and when combined with the "
"armament worn by this caste, the resulting warriors lack some of the typical "
"weaknesses of their kind, such as the strong vulnerability to spears and "
"arrows."
msgstr ""
"冲刺龙战士不会飞行和火息术，并常常假装善于近战战斗，是由于他们的无能。－虽然"
"曾经尝试过但这不是他们的责任。可能是由于他们稍微缺乏某项技能，但有这种理论，"
"他们不太善于和同类战斗。\n"
"\n"
"事实上，在他们内部的等级分类里，冲刺龙战士有大量的正规武器。他们并非不起作"
"用，在几次遭遇战中，发现他们天生的大个头和力量是强有力的武器，但他们也易受一"
"些武器的攻击，例如矛和箭。"

#: data/units/Drake_Enforcer.cfg:3
msgid "Drake Enforcer"
msgstr "重甲龙战士"

#: data/units/Drake_Enforcer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The great Drake Enforcers epitomize the raw strength of their kind. Long "
"hours at the forge have provided them with a bristling array of weaponry, "
"and have clad them head to toe in shining armor."
msgstr ""
"全部重甲龙战士的力量只有同族的一半。由于长时间在锻造车间，他们制造并自己使用"
"锋利的武器，和从头到脚的全身铠甲。"

#: data/units/Drake_Fighter.cfg:3
msgid "Drake Fighter"
msgstr "龙斗士"

#: data/units/Drake_Fighter.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Drake Fighters wield curved scimitars with deadly skill, and possess the "
"fire breathing skills of their ancestors. The most skilled Fighters go on to "
"join the ranks of the elite Drake Warriors."
msgstr ""
"龙斗士通过弯刀来使用致命技能，并有遗传下来的龙息术。大多数有能力的龙斗士加入"
"精英等级的龙勇士部队。"

#: data/units/Drake_Fighter.cfg:76
msgid "scimitar"
msgstr "弯刀"

#: data/units/Drake_Fire.cfg:3
msgid "Fire Drake"
msgstr "火龙战士"

#: data/units/Drake_Fire.cfg:31
msgid ""
"The great fire drakes are masters of their internal fire. Clad in shining "
"armor, they belch columns of flame at any who oppose them, a testament to "
"the strength and majesty of their kind."
msgstr ""
"全部的火龙战士都是善于用火作战的大师。穿着光亮的铠甲，他们会对敌人噴出一列火"
"海，在他们的种族中有着强大的力量和威严。"

#: data/units/Drake_Flameheart.cfg:3
msgid "Drake Flameheart"
msgstr "火心龙战士"

#: data/units/Drake_Flameheart.cfg:38
msgid ""
"It is said that the eldest lines of drakes - the direct descendants of the "
"dragons themselves, have veins which course with fire rather than blood. "
"That they can breathe fire as they do lends credence to this belief, though, "
"for some reason, no one has tried cutting one open to find out.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the leadership of a Flameheart enables friendly units next to "
"it to deal more damage in combat, though this only applies to units of lower "
"level."
msgstr ""
"这是排行第一的龙战士 － 古代龙的直系后代，体内的火比血还多。他们能够随意吐火"
"正如他们所信仰的那样，由于一些愿意，没人去问为什么。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：有领导能力的火心龙战士在战斗中会让相邻单位造成更多伤害，但只适合于"
"低等级单位。"

#: data/units/Drake_Flare.cfg:3
msgid "Drake Flare"
msgstr "闪耀龙战士"

#: data/units/Drake_Flare.cfg:37
msgid ""
"Drakes are an old race, wise enough to hearken to their own natural leaders. "
"Those who are called 'flares' by their enemies are the drakes who aspire to "
"be such leaders, both in war and in peace.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the leadership of a Flare enables friendly units next to it "
"to deal more damage in combat, though this only applies to units of lower "
"level."
msgstr ""
"这个一个古老的种族，听命于他们自己天生的领袖。这些被他们的敌人称之为‘闪耀龙战"
"士’，无论在战争或和平中都立志于当领袖。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：有领导能力的闪耀龙战士在战斗中会让相邻单位造成更多伤害，但只适合于"
"低等级单位。"

#: data/units/Drake_Gladiator.cfg:3
msgid "Drake Gladiator"
msgstr "龙斗剑士"

#: data/units/Drake_Gladiator.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The Gladiator has taken a completely different path from the Slashers. "
"Rather than emphasize training, they have chosen to focus on the craft of "
"their weaponry. They are the smiths of Drake society, and it follows that "
"they possess the best weaponry - the sharpest blades and spears, and the "
"maces which complement their already impressive array. Their intense focus "
"on their weapons comes at the slight expense of their defensive abilities."
msgstr ""
"龙斗剑士完全不同于斗殴者。除了强调训练外，他们还热衷于打造自己的武器。他们是"
"龙族里的铁匠，这让他们拥有最棒的武器 － 锋利的剑和矛，和那些给人印象深刻的"
"锤。他们太在意武器而让他们的防御不太好。"

#: data/units/Drake_Glider.cfg:3
msgid "Drake Glider"
msgstr "滑翔龙战士"

#: data/units/Drake_Glider.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Drake Gliders wear as little armor as possible so they can quickly escape "
"their foes when they leave their caves. These Drakes are competent fighters, "
"possessing the internal fire common to many of their kin. Gliders can also "
"effectively use their speed to viciously slam their opponents into "
"submission. The best gliders can look forward to being accepted into the "
"ranks of the high flying Sky Drakes."
msgstr ""
"这些龙战士穿着极少的铠甲，使他们离开洞穴后能快速的从敌人单位身边逃走。他们能"
"成为战士，且有内在遗传下的运用火的能力。他们也能有效的利用速度给予敌人致命般"
"的猛击。最好的滑翔龙战士能加入䒈高级飞龙精英部队。"

#: data/units/Drake_Glider.cfg:78 data/units/Drake_Hurricane.cfg:82
#: data/units/Drake_Sky.cfg:83
msgid "slam"
msgstr "猛击"

#: data/units/Drake_Hurricane.cfg:3
msgid "Hurricane Drake"
msgstr "飓风龙战士"

#: data/units/Drake_Hurricane.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Masters of the aerial realm, the Hurricane Drakes are the elite amongst "
"those drakes which are gifted with flight. Soaring high in the air, they can "
"see past most defensive cover and spit fire at their foes with impunity."
msgstr ""
"空中领域的大师，飓风龙战士是飞龙战士中的精英。在高耸入云的天空中，他们能获得"
"足够的防御并对敌人吐火而不受惩罚。"

#: data/units/Drake_Inferno.cfg:3
msgid "Inferno Drake"
msgstr "地狱龙战士"

#: data/units/Drake_Inferno.cfg:32
msgid ""
"The flying configurations known as Drake Infernos are the masters of the "
"fire they breathe, and rival their predecessors the Dragons in their ability "
"to use it. This natural ability renders them nearly immune to fire. Their "
"shining, flame-colored armor is a mark of their proud and powerful caste, "
"the ideal to which their brethren aspire."
msgstr ""
"这些有着能飞行构造的地狱龙战士是用火的大师，吐火是他们的天赋技能。这天生的技"
"能使得他们可以免疫火。他们光亮，火红色的铠甲是他们值得骄傲和强大能力的团体的"
"标志，这个他们朋友最渴望的东西。"

#: data/units/Drake_Sky.cfg:3
msgid "Sky Drake"
msgstr "飞龙战士"

#: data/units/Drake_Sky.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Sky drakes are truly the kings of the sky. Using their momentum and fire "
"breath as weapons these drakes are the bane of many. They can swiftly swoop "
"down on prey, and are usually long gone before anyone can stop them."
msgstr ""
"飞龙战士是事实上的空中之王。运用他们的能力和火息术是敌人的祸根。他们能很快的"
"向牺牲者俯冲，并在任何人能阻止他们之前而早已离去。"

#: data/units/Drake_Slasher.cfg:4
msgid "Drake Slasher"
msgstr "斗殴龙战士"

#: data/units/Drake_Slasher.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Slashers are clashers who have chosen to master the use of a Halberd instead "
"of carrying a sword and the spear. Their great size allows them to use a "
"weapon of matching scale, large enough to skewer a horse as a man would a "
"boar. Their training has also enhanced their stamina and defensive skills, "
"which is a major advantage over their close cousins the Gladiators."
msgstr ""
"斗殴龙战士是一群选择戟来代替剑和矛来作为主要武器。由于他们足够大的身体，使得"
"他们的武器可以象串猪一样来串马和人。训练会提高他们的耐力和防御力，这是和龙斗"
"剑士近战中主要的优势。"

#: data/units/Drake_Slasher.cfg:75 data/units/Drake_Slasher.cfg:95
#: data/units/Drake_Warden.cfg:79 data/units/Drake_Warden.cfg:99
#: data/units/Halbardier.cfg:34 data/units/Halbardier.cfg:75
msgid "halberd"
msgstr "戟"

#: data/units/Drake_Slasher.cfg:98 data/units/Drake_Warden.cfg:102
#: data/units/Goblin_Impaler.cfg:35 data/units/Halbardier.cfg:40
#: data/units/Javelineer.cfg:34 data/units/Pikeman.cfg:63
#: data/units/Spearman.cfg:66
msgid "firststrike"
msgstr "先攻权"

#: data/units/Drake_Warden.cfg:4
msgid "Drake Warden"
msgstr "龙守卫"

#: data/units/Drake_Warden.cfg:26
msgid ""
"The Warden represents the pinnacle of the clasher caste, being picked from "
"the most able Slashers. They have forged their might such that few warriors "
"on this earth would dare stand against them. The Wardens' weapon of choice "
"is the halberd, which they use to great effect."
msgstr ""
"龙守卫非常善于用尖锐的武器进行攻击，通常选至于斗殴龙。他们拥有足够的权力，只"
"有很少一部分勇士敢挑战他们。龙守卫的武器是戟，这种他们非常善于运用的武器。"

#: data/units/Drake_Warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Drake Warrior"
msgstr "龙勇士"

#: data/units/Drake_Warrior.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Drake Warriors wield swords with great skill, and possess the fire breathing "
"skills of their ancestors. The great strength of their kind allows them to "
"strike withering blows, and to withstand punishment in equal measure."
msgstr ""
"龙勇士拥有强大的剑技能，并继承了龙息术。强大的力量能让他们进行有效的打击，并"
"能承受相同的惩罚。"

#: data/units/Draug.cfg:3
msgid "Draug"
msgstr "龙神"

#: data/units/Draug.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Towering remains of what once were legendary warriors, the Draug strike fear "
"in the hearts of all who oppose them. They are driven not by malice, but are "
"forever bound within the dream of unlife, wandering through the greatest "
"battles of their memory, and fighting desperately for release, for a peace "
"bought only by strength of arms. The memory of their enemy, and the purpose "
"of their struggle have long faded into oblivion."
msgstr ""
"在高耸的遗迹里曾经有着传说中的勇士，龙神会让他们的对手深深的惧怕。他们是没有"
"恶意的，在那永无止境超于生命的梦境，徘徊在伟大战役的记忆里，并不顾一切的战斗"
"着，由强劲武器带来的和平。在他们敌人的记忆里，他们努力斗争的过去以渐渐远去。"

#: data/units/Draug.cfg:46 data/units/Dwarvish_Fighter.cfg:28
#: data/units/Revenant.cfg:45 data/units/Skeleton.cfg:46
msgid "axe"
msgstr "斧"

#: data/units/Duelist.cfg:3
msgid "Duelist"
msgstr "青卫队"

#: data/units/Duelist.cfg:29
msgid ""
"It is a peculiar fashion of Wesnoth's nobility, in that they typically "
"enroll their sons into one of two orders of armigers, training them either "
"in the art of horsemanship, or fencing. Duelists are so named for an "
"unfortunately common practice of young aristocrats, for whom the heat of "
"insult can sometimes incite a rash demonstration of their natural right.\n"
"\n"
"Experienced fencers, who often look the part of nobility if not always "
"actually of noble birth, carry with them a small crossbow that is easily "
"concealed under a coat or cape. Slow to load and often thought dishonorable "
"to use, it is in fact very useful, and those of their ranks who live long "
"enough to be veterans typically do so by making such concessions to utility "
"and survival.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: their skill at skirmishing allows these fencers to dart right "
"past an opponent, ignoring zones of control."
msgstr ""
"这是韦诺贵族里特殊的现象。他们通常让自己的儿子加入两个贤明神职单位之一。训练"
"他们马术和剑术技艺。青卫队很不幸由练习中的青年贵族所组成而命名，他们有时会为"
"自然权力而进行鲁莽的攻击。\n"
"\n"
"常常注意着部分贵族的老练的剑术家，如果那些不是真正天生的贵族，则很容易隐藏弩"
"弓在外套或斗篷下。慢慢装载和不善于使用的，这些现象是非常明显，这些人中有足够"
"等级的会标记为正式军人和能够幸存。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：他们的侦察技能使得他们很容易的绕过敌军，并忽略可控制区域。"

#: data/units/Duelist.cfg:75 data/units/Fencer.cfg:79
#: data/units/Master_at_Arms.cfg:40
#, fuzzy
msgid "sabre"
msgstr "戳"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Berserker.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Berserker"
msgstr "矮人狂暴者"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Berserker.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Dwarves are an ancient race of powerful fighters. Their Berserkers forget "
"all defense in exchange for massive damage against their enemies. Once a "
"battle is entered, Dwarvish Berserkers attack ferociously, continuing to "
"push the attack until either they or their enemy lies dead."
msgstr ""
"矮人是一个古老且善于战斗的强力种族。这些狂暴者在战斗中忽略防御来换得最大攻击"
"力。一点战斗开始，矮人狂暴者在战斗中很凶猛，知道杀死对方或自己。"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Berserker.cfg:33 data/units/Dwarvish_Ulfserker.cfg:32
msgid "berserker frenzy"
msgstr "疯狂狂暴者"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Berserker.cfg:36 data/units/Dwarvish_Ulfserker.cfg:35
msgid "berserk"
msgstr "狂暴"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Dragonguard.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Dragonguard"
msgstr "矮人龙守卫"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Dragonguard.cfg:23
msgid ""
"It is not clear why the Dragonguards are called what they are, a name given "
"by their dwarven brethren. Some speculate that the name comes from their "
"weapon of choice, these strange staves that belch fire and death. Others "
"have surmised that it is because such weapons would be a threat against even "
"a true Dragon, should such a thing be seen again in the known world. "
"Whatever the case, it is for these weapons that the guardians of the great "
"Dwarven citadels are both renowned and feared; weapons that have broken the "
"mightiest of warriors in a single blow."
msgstr ""
"这些龙守卫并不十分清楚为什么他们的矮人朋友会给他们起这个名字。一些认为是由于"
"武器的选择，这些奇怪的装置放出火焰和死亡气息。另一些认为是武器能吓退那些能在"
"真实世界能见到的龙。无论外表如何，这些武器会让矮人守卫者获得尊重和畏惧而得以"
"自保：能在一次攻击里杀死强力的勇士。"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Dragonguard.cfg:27
#: data/units/Dwarvish_Dragonguard.cfg:47
msgid "dragonstaff"
msgstr "龙棍"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Fighter.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Fighter"
msgstr "矮人战士"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Fighter.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Dwarvish Fighters wield mighty battle axes and hammers, which make them "
"feared opponents in close range combat. They are excellent in mountainous "
"terrain or underground. Though not swift, their power and endurance more "
"than compensate."
msgstr ""
"矮人在战斗中使用斧和锤，让敌人在近战中惧怕。他们适合在山脉和地下世界作战。虽"
"然不够迅捷，他们的强力和高耐力能够弥补。"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Fighter.cfg:47 data/units/Dwarvish_Lord.cfg:53
#: data/units/Dwarvish_Steelclad.cfg:53 data/units/Troll_Warrior.cfg:32
msgid "hammer"
msgstr "锤"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Guardsman.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Guardsman"
msgstr "矮人守卫者"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Guardsman.cfg:29
msgid ""
"The most resilient dwarves sometimes join the Dwarvish army as Guardsmen. "
"Slow and without a strong attack, they guard the Army's flank, soaking up a "
"lot of damage, and hurling heavy spears for defense."
msgstr ""
"大多数有恢复能力的矮人会加入矮人军队如守卫者。慢速且没强力攻击，他们保护军队"
"的侧面，吸收许多伤害并投掷重矛来进行防御。"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Lord.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Lord"
msgstr "矮人王"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Lord.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Clad in shining armor, these dwarves look like kings from under the "
"mountains. They wield axe and hammer with masterful skill, and can hit a "
"target with a thrown hand axe at several paces. Though slow on their feet, "
"these dwarves are a testament to the prowess of their kin."
msgstr ""
"穿着光亮的铠甲，这些矮人看上去象来至于地下山脉的国王。他们以斧和锤作为主要技"
"能，并能在一定区域象目标投掷手斧。虽然移动速度很慢，但这些矮人继承了超凡的战"
"术。"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Lord.cfg:71
msgid "hatchet"
msgstr "手斧"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Runemaster.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Runemaster"
msgstr "矮人雕刻大师"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Runemaster.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Dwarven magic, inasmuch as is known, most often manifests itself by the "
"inscription of runes in the surface of an object, which by their mere "
"presence somehow imbue it with power. Though rarely seen in combat, a master "
"of these runes can put them to terrifying use."
msgstr ""
"矮人魔法师，据知，通常善于在物体表面雕琢符文，这些有时会附上不可知的力量。虽"
"然在战斗中很少见，大师则会用到很恐怖的地步。"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Runemaster.cfg:27
msgid "runic hammer"
msgstr "符文锤"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Runemaster.cfg:50
msgid "Lightning bolt"
msgstr "闪电箭"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Sentinel.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Sentinel"
msgstr "矮人哨兵"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Sentinel.cfg:37
msgid ""
"The Sentinel, with his tower shield and great courage, refuses to yield "
"under even the strongest of enemy attacks."
msgstr "哨兵，有着塔盾和强大胆量，拒绝屈服，即使是最强大的敌人的攻击。"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Stalwart.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Stalwart"
msgstr "矮人重甲兵"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Stalwart.cfg:32
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Stalwarts, after years in battle, have fashioned new shields and strong "
"armor from the ruins of their enemies. While slow, they are feared for their "
"resilience and strength."
msgstr ""
"重甲兵，在多年战斗之后，装备了从敌人处获得新盾和强力铠甲。虽然慢速，但以他们"
"的反弹攻击和力量而被敌人所惧怕。"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Steelclad.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Steelclad"
msgstr "矮人防御者"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Steelclad.cfg:30
msgid ""
"The more experienced Dwarvish Steelclad fighters wear heavy chain mail and "
"plate armor, for which they are rightly famous."
msgstr "许多老练的矮人防御者穿着锁链铠甲和板甲，他们以这而著称。"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Thunderer.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Thunderer"
msgstr "矮人雷霆战士"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Thunderer.cfg:22
msgid ""
"When the men of Wesnoth first encountered the dwarves, they were mystified "
"by the power of the Dwarvish Thunderers, who were able to hurl death from "
"afar through the apparatus of these strange ... 'wands' they carried into "
"battle. After the peace instituted by the Ka'lian came into effect, "
"Haldric's people, not understanding these weapons, and certainly unable to "
"make any of their own, realized they were lucky to no longer be fighting the "
"dwarves, and vowed never to do so again."
msgstr ""
"当人们在韦诺第一次碰到矮人时，他们常常困惑于这些矮人雷霆战士所使用的能力，这"
"些战士能从远处投掷出携带的奇怪...‘棒’来造成致命打击。当Ka'lian带来和平后，"
"Haldric的人们，不理解这些武器，且不能自己制作时，认识到自己非常幸运再也不必与"
"矮人们作战，并发誓永不发生。"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Thunderer.cfg:72
msgid "thunderstick"
msgstr "雷霆棍"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Thunderguard.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Thunderguard"
msgstr "矮人雷霆守卫者"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Thunderguard.cfg:25
msgid ""
"The Dwarven Thunderguards are famed for their curious weaponry, these "
"strange staves of wood and iron that make a thunderous noise in their anger. "
"The machinations behind this weaponry are a mystery, a secret taken to the "
"grave by the dwarves of Knalga who wield them, and are assumed to have even "
"forged them. The most that is known are reports of dwarves pouring a strange "
"black dust into the mouth of their weapons, which some say is a food to fuel "
"the beast imprisoned within.\n"
"\n"
"Though a single shot from these 'thundersticks' can take several minutes to "
"prepare, the results are seen by the Dwarves as being well worth the wait."
msgstr ""
"矮人雷霆守卫者以他们古怪的武器著称于世，当他们发怒时这由木头和铁片组成的棒会"
"发出雷鸣般的声响。这武器的构成是个迷，最后会被秘密带入Knalga世界矮人拥有者的"
"坟墓里，并声称已被熔炼。为世人所知的是，矮人把一些黑色粉末放入他们武器的入口"
"出，并说是用来喂养里面的野兽。\n"
"\n"
"虽然用‘雷霆棒’攻击一次需要等待片刻，但结果确实矮人们可以接受的。"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Thunderguard.cfg:58
msgid "dragonstick"
msgstr "龙棍"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Ulfserker.cfg:3
msgid "Dwarvish Ulfserker"
msgstr "矮人双手斧战士"

#: data/units/Dwarvish_Ulfserker.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Dwarves are an ancient race of powerful fighters. Ulfserkers are the most "
"ferocious of these in battle: they persist until either their enemy is dead "
"or they themselves perish, no matter how many wounds they receive."
msgstr ""
"矮人是一支古老善战的种族。双手斧战士是最残暴的战士：他们持续攻击直到杀死敌"
"人，或毁灭他们自己，无论多重的伤他们都能承受。"

#: data/units/Elder_Wose.cfg:3
msgid "Elder Wose"
msgstr "长老树人"

#: data/units/Elder_Wose.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Woses have been said to possess many shapes, all of them tree-like in form, "
"and as they age, to increase in size. Tales tell of woses who resemble trees "
"in this respect as well, towering over the creatures who walk beneath them. "
"This is the greater part of why they are so rarely seen - standing in the "
"slumber which they so often do, a wose of that stature appears to be nothing "
"more than an oddly-shaped tree. Even a careless elf can sometimes be "
"fooled.\n"
"\n"
"Woses are not warriors by any means, however the strength they possess is "
"obviously capable of violence, should someone manage to raise the ire of "
"these creatures.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Woses regenerate by using natural resources around them, "
"without needing to huddle in villages to obtain sustenance and aid."
msgstr ""
"树人有很多形状，但他们都长得像树。他们的身材也会随着年龄而增长。正如树人长的"
"像树，在这种情况下，走在他们下面的人都不会察觉。这也是他们不长见的原因之一，"
"树人站在那里就像一颗树，即使最小心的精灵有时也会被愚弄。\n"
"\n"
"树人没有什么勇士，但强大的力量足以让他们进行战斗，如果有人惹他们的话。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：树人通过使用周围的自然资源来重生，就不需要呆在村庄或要食物和支援。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Archer.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Archer"
msgstr "精灵弓箭手"

#: data/units/Elvish_Archer.cfg:34
msgid ""
"Elves have always had a reputation for archery, a skill that, for many "
"reasons, comes naturally to them. Even the frail of body can be deadly with "
"a bow in hand, and in times of war, many will take up this weapon. Though "
"their relative inexperience with combat leaves them somewhat vulnerable, "
"their natural grace ensures that they can best any of humanity's fresh "
"recruits."
msgstr ""
"精灵常常以善于箭术而闻名，这个技能就像与生俱来的。即使虚弱的身体会由手中的弓"
"而死亡，但在战争中，许多精灵会拿起他们的武器。虽然没什么战斗经验使得他们有时"
"在战斗中处于不利地位，但天性优雅使得他们成为人类朋友最好的征兵对象。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Archer.cfg:123
msgid "female^Elvish Archer"
msgstr "女性精灵弓箭手"

#: data/units/Elvish_Avenger.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Avenger"
msgstr "精灵复仇者"

#: data/units/Elvish_Avenger.cfg:43
msgid ""
"The curious name of the elvish 'Avengers' comes from a tactic often employed "
"by these master rangers. The enemy is allowed to break through a feint "
"defense, and when the vulnerable troops behind the front line follow, these "
"archers break cover and attack, cutting the supply lines and surrounding the "
"enemy in one fell stroke.\n"
"\n"
"This has, at times, been interpreted as a form of vengeance for their "
"brethren lost earlier in the battle. Although not so base in design, it is "
"not at all inaccurate.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the avengers' skill as woodsmen render them invisible to an "
"enemy unless they are immediately adjacent, or have revealed themselves by "
"attacking."
msgstr ""
"精灵‘复仇者’的名号通常来至于那些巡林客的一项战术。敌人通常被一些伪装的防御体"
"所迷惑，当易受攻击的部队来到前线是，这些弓箭手就突破掩护并攻击，切断补给线然"
"后给予敌人一回合致命打击。\n"
"\n"
"这些复仇者在之前的战斗中失去兄弟后，就会发起这样的攻势。虽然没有事先设计，但"
"是很精准。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：复仇者的技能使得他们在森林中不会被敌人单位看见直到相邻，或战斗后显"
"露自己。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Avenger.cfg:140
msgid "female^Elvish Avenger"
msgstr "女性精灵复仇者"

#: data/units/Elvish_Captain.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Captain"
msgstr "精灵首领"

#: data/units/Elvish_Captain.cfg:40
msgid ""
"Elves, unlike many other races, will quickly acknowledge and follow any of "
"their peers who have experience in combat. This is quite at odds with "
"humanity, for whom leadership is often a fickle mess of coercion and "
"intimidation. The combination of their willingness to accept the wisdom of "
"their leaders, and the tendency to choose leaders of merit is one of the "
"quiet strengths of the elves.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the leadership of a Captain enables friendly units next to it "
"to deal more damage in combat, though this only applies to units of lower "
"level."
msgstr ""
"精灵不像其他种族，十分愿意并更随那些有战斗经验的同类。这不同于人类，那些靠高"
"压统治的领袖。他们非常乐于接受贤人作为他们的领袖。倾向于接受十分有实力和优点"
"的精灵作为领袖。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：首领的领导才能使得相邻的友好单位在战斗中能造成更多伤害，但只对低等"
"级有效。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Champion.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Champion"
msgstr "精灵拥护者"

#: data/units/Elvish_Champion.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Those few elves who deliberately hone themselves into weapons of war become "
"something which belies the rather docile reputation of their race. "
"Dedication and skill are matched with purity of form, and the result is a "
"mastery of swordsmanship to which few can compare. Even archery, treated as "
"a secondary pursuit, is executed with a skill that most of humanity can only "
"stare at with wonder."
msgstr ""
"这些极少数精灵刻意磨练战斗中的剑术技能，成为那些有辱这个种族名声的一类。但是"
"这些奉献所得则是无与伦比的剑术。即使是作为第二技能的箭术，也没有多少人类能与"
"之匹敌。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Druid.cfg:3
msgid "female^Elvish Druid"
msgstr "女性精灵德鲁伊"

#: data/units/Elvish_Druid.cfg:32
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The magic of the wood elves is poorly suited for combat, but effective "
"nonetheless. The forests in which they live can be quickened by a word of "
"command, and will lash out at those who threaten their peace.\n"
"\n"
"Their chief ability lies in healing, and it is for this skill that the "
"elvish druids are revered by their people.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: A druid's entangling attack slows enemies down, halving their "
"movement speed and attack damage. Druids are capable of healing units around "
"them, and curing them of poison."
msgstr ""
"木精灵的魔法不太适合战斗，但也不一定。在他们所居住的森林里能激发他们的潜能，"
"使那些破坏他们和平的人吃不消。\n"
"\n"
"他们的主要技能是治疗，并由于这种技能被精灵族所敬重。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：卷入战争的精灵能降低敌人的速度，并减低他们所造成的伤害。德鲁伊有治"
"疗相邻单位，并治愈中毒的能力。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Druid.cfg:55 data/units/Elvish_Shyde.cfg:65
msgid "ensnare"
msgstr "陷阱"

#: data/units/Elvish_Druid.cfg:78 data/units/Elvish_Shyde.cfg:88
msgid "thorns"
msgstr "荆棘"

#: data/units/Elvish_Enchantress.cfg:3
msgid "female^Elvish Enchantress"
msgstr "女性精灵女巫"

#: data/units/Elvish_Enchantress.cfg:35
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Elven Enchantresses are masters of offensive magic, striking at their "
"enemies both with blasts of icy wind drawn from the ethereal plane, and "
"magically animating roots with which they bind their enemies in place."
msgstr ""
"精灵女巫擅长于魔法攻击，对敌人造成面攻击性冰冻爆炸伤害，和用魔法树根困住敌"
"人。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Enchantress.cfg:81 data/units/Elvish_Shaman.cfg:57
#: data/units/Elvish_Sorceress.cfg:81
msgid "entangle"
msgstr "缠绕"

#: data/units/Elvish_Fighter.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Fighter"
msgstr "精灵战士"

#: data/units/Elvish_Fighter.cfg:34
msgid ""
"Elves are not warlike by nature, but in times of need, their natural grace "
"and agility serve them well, as does their skillful craftsmanship. An elf "
"can grasp the basics of swordsmanship and archery in an uncannily short "
"time, and put them to effective use on the battlefield."
msgstr ""
"精灵并非天生好战，但需要时，他们的优雅天性和机敏会帮他们，作用于他们熟练的技"
"能上。精灵掌握着基础的箭术和神秘短促的剑术，使得在战场中很有效。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Hero.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Hero"
msgstr "精灵英雄"

#: data/units/Elvish_Hero.cfg:34
msgid ""
"A relatively small amount of experience will turn an elf from a competent "
"fighter into a master of combat. Those who are honored as heroes are strong "
"with both sword and bow, skills that never fade for lack of practice."
msgstr ""
"精灵只需很少的经验就能成为由战士成长为战斗大师。这些英雄有着强大的剑和弓技"
"能，且不会随着时间流逝而荒废。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Marksman.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Marksman"
msgstr "精灵神射手"

#: data/units/Elvish_Marksman.cfg:39
msgid ""
"One of the things which contributes to their skill with the bow is the "
"unusually clear vision of elves. An elf practiced at archery can hit targets "
"that a man couldn't even see, even at night, and can nock a second arrow "
"almost as soon as the first is let fly.\n"
"\n"
"This prodigious skill does come with one cost, that being a lack of practice "
"with the sword.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Their marksmanship gives these elves a high chance of hitting "
"their enemy, but only on the attack."
msgstr ""
"精灵清晰的眼睛是他们善于弓技能的要素之一。有经验的精灵能让敌人看不见他们，即"
"使是在晚上，并能接二连三的射出箭。\n"
"\n"
"这惊人的技能也使得他们不擅长用剑。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：他们的射击术给予了精灵对敌人很高的打击比率，但仅仅在攻击时。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Marksman.cfg:82 data/units/Elvish_Sharpshooter.cfg:82
msgid "longbow"
msgstr "长弓"

#: data/units/Elvish_Marksman.cfg:142
msgid "female^Elvish Marksman"
msgstr "女性精灵神射手"

#: data/units/Elvish_Marshal.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Marshal"
msgstr "精灵元帅"

#: data/units/Elvish_Marshal.cfg:41
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The longevity and natural intelligence of elves makes for a vicious aptitude "
"for military matters, enough even to counter their general distaste for such "
"things. Elves remember things much more clearly than humankind, and can "
"often intuit what others can only be trained to do. Certainly, on those rare "
"occasions when an elf sets his mind to war, the strategy that results is the "
"work of a master.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the leadership of a Marshal enables friendly units next to it "
"to deal more damage in combat, though this only applies to units of lower "
"level"
msgstr ""
"长寿和天资聪颖的精灵能习得足够的军事技能，技能是通常他们厌恶的方面。精灵比人"
"类记事更清楚，并能感知那些人能被训练。确定的是，当他们极其罕见的出现在战争中"
"时，即成为战略大师。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：元帅的领导技能使得相邻单位在战斗中能造成更多伤害，但仅对低级单位有"
"效。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Outrider.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Outrider"
msgstr "精灵骑射手"

#: data/units/Elvish_Outrider.cfg:41
msgid ""
"Elvish Outriders are trained as the royal couriers of the elven kingdoms. "
"Despite the peaceful nature of their people, their experience makes them "
"quite deadly in combat. No man has ever come close to their skill in using a "
"bow on horseback - in fact, most would be hard pressed to equal it standing "
"on solid ground.\n"
"\n"
"The speed of these soldiers allows the elves to strike when and where they "
"choose when fighting on their home ground, a fact that has saved many of "
"their number from death."
msgstr ""
"精灵骑射手被训练成为精灵王国的信使。尽管他们是爱好和平人士，但是经验使得他们"
"很擅战。他们在马背上使用弓技能时没有人能靠近他们 － 事实上，大多数在坚固土地"
"上的他们是很难缠的对手。\n"
"\n"
"速度训练使得他们在家园内无论何时何地都可以自由攻击，这挽救了很大数量的人们免"
"于死亡。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Ranger.cfg:2
msgid "Elvish Ranger"
msgstr "精灵巡林客"

#: data/units/Elvish_Ranger.cfg:40
msgid ""
"Though a man might spend years in the forest, he will never shake the "
"feeling that he is a guest in a place he is not truly a part of. With elves, "
"this is quite reversed. Any elf that studies the lore of the woods becomes a "
"fitting master of them, and when combined with a considerable skill at "
"archery and swordsmanship, the result is a powerful tool of war.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the rangers' skill as woodsmen render them invisible to an "
"enemy unless they are immediately adjacent, or have revealed themselves by "
"attacking."
msgstr ""
"一个人即使在森林里很多年，也会一直认为他是精灵领地的过客。许多精灵象精灵之王"
"学习成为使用射击和剑术的战斗大师，这结果在战斗中是很有用的。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：巡林客的技能使得他们可以在敌人面前隐藏行踪知道彼此相邻，或他们开始"
"攻击。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Ranger.cfg:139
msgid "female^Elvish Ranger"
msgstr "女性精灵巡林客"

#: data/units/Elvish_Rider.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Rider"
msgstr "精灵骑兵"

#: data/units/Elvish_Rider.cfg:44
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The master horsemen of the elves are able to move through forests at a speed "
"which would be suicidal to any man. Though this certainly leaves people in "
"awe of the rider, questions have also been raised about the stock of the "
"horses, for the feats they perform seem almost supernatural.\n"
"\n"
"This combination of incredible mobility and potent combat strength is one of "
"the greatest assets the elves possess in warfare."
msgstr ""
"马背上的精灵大师能够在森里以让人疯狂的速度随意移动。虽然确实让他们骑士感到敬"
"畏，问题是得提高马的血统来适应他们的超常能力。\n"
"\n"
"这难以置信的移动组合和强力战斗技能是精灵族最有价值的资产之一。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Scout.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Scout"
msgstr "精灵侦察兵"

#: data/units/Elvish_Scout.cfg:42
msgid ""
"The horsemen of the wood elves have some skill with bow and sword, but their "
"true skill lies in their horsemanship. Even other elves are somewhat taken "
"by their uncanny speed in the woods, and their ability to dart through the "
"thick of the forest with nary a scratch. They are, perhaps, some of the only "
"cavalry in existence that fares better in the woods than on open ground."
msgstr ""
"这些马背上的木精灵会使用弓和剑，但这些技能依赖来他们的马技。有时其他的精灵也"
"诧异于他们在森林里怪诞的速度，并且急速行走也不会在森林里被抓伤。可能他们是唯"
"一一个在森林比平原更善战的单位。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Shaman.cfg:3
msgid "female^Elvish Shaman"
msgstr "女性精灵萨满法师"

#: data/units/Elvish_Shaman.cfg:33
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Being partly faerie in nature, elves have an inherent capability for magic. "
"This is realized in their affinity with the natural world, which they can "
"call upon as an ally in combat. Enemies wandering in their forests may soon "
"find themselves entangled by the very roots they stand on, making them much "
"less of a threat.\n"
"\n"
"The healing abilities of the elves are also remarkable, and of capital use "
"in battle.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: A shaman's entangling attack slows enemies down, halving "
"their movement speed and attack damage. Shamans are capable of basic "
"healing, though they can only delay the effects of poison, not cure them "
"entirely."
msgstr ""
"在这仙境一般的世界里，精灵有着与生俱来的魔法能力。他们能运用周围的自然力量在"
"战斗。敌人容易发现在森林里会被脚下的树根缠绕住，这可是不小的威胁。\n"
"\n"
"精灵的治疗技能也是值得关注的，战斗中是主要的技能。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：萨满法师能使敌人减速并降低他们的攻击速度，萨满只会基本的治疗法术，"
"所以他们只能延缓中毒效果而不能治愈。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Sharpshooter.cfg:3
msgid "Elvish Sharpshooter"
msgstr "精灵神枪手"

#: data/units/Elvish_Sharpshooter.cfg:38
msgid ""
"A story once wandered about, of an elf who stopped an arrow by shooting it "
"out of the air with one of his own. It is a testament to the skill of the "
"elves that such a story could be taken seriously. The sharpshooters of the "
"elves have, quite simply, mastered the art of archery.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Their marksmanship gives these elves a high chance of hitting "
"their enemy, but only on the attack."
msgstr ""
"有个故事这么说，一个精灵能抓住他们已射出的箭。这天赋技能不会因为一个故事而成"
"真。精灵神枪手，很简单，就是射击大师。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：射击技能使得他们对敌人有很高的击中比率，但仅在攻击时。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Sharpshooter.cfg:142
msgid "female^Elvish Sharpshooter"
msgstr "女性精灵神枪手"

#: data/units/Elvish_Shyde.cfg:3
msgid "female^Elvish Shyde"
msgstr "女性精灵仙子"

#: data/units/Elvish_Shyde.cfg:32
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Devotion to her faerie side will eventually transform an elf maiden into a "
"creature of both worlds. Guided by a nature which is little understood, "
"these beautiful stewards of the elven forests epitomize the grace and "
"mystery of their people.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: A shyde's entangling attack slows enemies down, halving their "
"movement speed and attack damage. Shydes are capable of healing units around "
"them, and curing them of poison."
msgstr ""
"热衷于仙境使得精灵少女成为两个世界共有的生物。引导自然的能力是不难理解的，这"
"些漂亮的精灵仙子成为森林里他们族神秘和优雅的一部分。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：精灵仙子可以减低敌人速度并减慢敌人的攻击频率。她们能治疗相邻的单"
"位，并治愈中毒。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Shyde.cfg:36 data/units/Elvish_Sylph.cfg:31
msgid "faerie touch"
msgstr "仙境触觉"

#: data/units/Elvish_Sorceress.cfg:3
msgid "female^Elvish Sorceress"
msgstr "女性精灵术士"

#: data/units/Elvish_Sorceress.cfg:35
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Eschewing the study of healing in favor of more aggressive uses of magic, "
"Elvish Sorceresses have become quite proficient at ranged combat. Their "
"entangling attack is notably more effective than that of the Elvish Shaman, "
"and they can call upon bursts of chilling ethereal wind to smite those who "
"oppose them."
msgstr ""
"疏于学习治疗技能而爱好战斗魔法，精灵术士变得十分精通于远程战斗。他们在战争中"
"的能力更甚从前，并能给敌人以冰冷爆炸打击。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Sylph.cfg:3
#, fuzzy
msgid "female^Elvish Sylph"
msgstr "女性精灵少妇"

#: data/units/Elvish_Sylph.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Elvish Sylphs are scions of beauty in the mortal plane. Having fully "
"developed their faerie side, they transform into creatures of both worlds, "
"wielding powerful magic against their enemies."
msgstr ""
"精灵少妇是生物位面漂亮的一支。完全研究仙境力量，使得他们成为两个世界共有的生"
"物。并能对敌人运用强力的魔法攻击。"

#: data/units/Elvish_Sylph.cfg:60
msgid "gossamer"
msgstr "蛛丝"

#: data/units/Fencer.cfg:3
msgid "Fencer"
msgstr "剑术师"

#: data/units/Fencer.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Fencers belong to a school of thought that considers the armor most soldiers "
"wear in combat to be their own worst enemy. While armor can only soften a "
"blow, evading it will completely negate any ill effects. Being able to "
"reliably dodge any offensive move is a luxury only afforded to the fit of "
"body, and then only to those who endure rigorous training.\n"
"\n"
"Outfitted with only a dagger and rapier, fencers are light on their feet and "
"useful in many situations where their armor-bound peers are at a "
"disadvantage. They relish, often literally, in dancing circles around troops "
"like heavy infantry, in mockery of the price they pay for their full plate.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: their skill at skirmishing allows fencers to dart right past "
"an opponent, ignoring zones of control."
msgstr ""
"这些属于学校的剑术师认为士兵在战斗中穿着的铠甲是他们最大的敌人。铠甲只能降低"
"伤害，并非完全避免负面影响。要避开攻击是奢侈的，仅仅当穿着得当，和受到过足够"
"的耐力训练。\n"
"\n"
"仅仅配备匕首和双刃长剑，剑术师有着轻便的步伐和同类铠甲战士在弱势情况下是，他"
"依然能处于有利状态。他们喜好在象重甲步兵这样的部队周围跳舞，嘲弄他们为全身铠"
"而付出的代价。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：他们的侦察技能允许他们从敌人身边轻易走过，并忽略控制地带。"

#: data/units/Footpad.cfg:3
msgid "Footpad"
msgstr "拦路强盗"

#: data/units/Footpad.cfg:23
msgid ""
"These petty criminals are often derisively called 'footpads' by their "
"superiors, for they are tasked with any job that requires a great deal of "
"running around, often being employed as couriers, or scouts. The endurance "
"and skill on their feet that comes of this serves them well in combat, and "
"despite their pitiable weaponry, they are quite good at harrying their "
"enemies, especially under cover of darkness."
msgstr ""
"小偷小摸的人常被他们的上级称为‘拦路强盗’，并被给予很多需要到处跑动的工作，如"
"信使或侦察兵。脚步耐力和技能使得他们善于战斗，尽管有着很烂的武器，他们仍很擅"
"长折磨敌人，特别是在夜幕掩护之下。"

#: data/units/Footpad.cfg:26 data/units/Thug.cfg:26 data/units/Troll.cfg:31
#: data/units/Troll_Hero.cfg:31
msgid "club"
msgstr "木棒"

#: data/units/Footpad.cfg:78
msgid "female^Footpad"
msgstr "女性拦路强盗"

#: data/units/Galleon.cfg:4
msgid "Galleon"
msgstr "大帆船"

#: data/units/Galleon.cfg:18
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Even people happily living in their homes eventually need some kind of "
"transport through the seas, even if only to go fishing or to trade goods. "
"The galleon is perfect for this purpose: it's fast and resilient, but not "
"prepared to fight, and is able to adapt to many different tasks."
msgstr ""
"尽管人们乐于呆在家园但也需要一些航海技能，即使仅仅用来捕鱼或进行贸易。大帆船"
"很适合这些用途：快且富于弹性，但不适合作战，并能适应多种不同的用途。"

#: data/units/Galleon.cfg:20
msgid "dummy"
msgstr "傀儡"

#: data/units/General.cfg:3
msgid "General"
msgstr "将军"

#: data/units/General.cfg:41
msgid ""
"As the leaders of their armies, Generals are responsible for the protection "
"of large or important areas in the kingdoms they swore fealty to. Their "
"training and experience suffice to carry out these orders.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the leadership of a General enables friendly units next to it "
"to deal more damage in combat, though this only applies to units of lower "
"level."
msgstr ""
"作为军队的领袖，通常有能力在他所效忠的的王国内保护大片或重要的区域。他们所受"
"的训练和经验足够应付这些情况。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：将军的领导才能使得周围的单位能在战斗中造成更多伤害，但仅对低级单位"
"有效。"

#: data/units/Ghost.cfg:3
msgid "Ghost"
msgstr "幽灵"

#: data/units/Ghost.cfg:26
msgid ""
"It is one of the greater mercies of creation that a human soul is immutable, "
"and cannot be destroyed. However, the many things a necromancer can do, "
"despite this, are entirely horrifying.\n"
"\n"
"Trapped within a shroud of vile enchantments, a spirit likens unto the wind "
"in the sails of a ship. The contrivance that results from this prison is an "
"unfailing servant, which can be bound to whatever task their master sees "
"fit.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Ghosts have very unusual resistances to damage, and move "
"quite slowly over open water."
msgstr ""
"这是人类灵魂不朽之后强大的产物，且不会被摧毁。然而，死灵法师能够震退他们。\n"
"\n"
"陷入邪恶妖法的灵魂，就如同船上的风帆。这在监狱之下成功改造成无说畏惧的仆人，"
"被他们的主人用于任何合适的任务。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：幽灵对很多伤害都有不凡抗性，且在水面上移动很慢。"

#: data/units/Ghoul.cfg:3
msgid "Ghoul"
msgstr "食尸鬼"

#: data/units/Ghoul.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Only those who have delved into the circles of necromancy know what must be "
"done to turn a person into a ghoul, and it is a secret they are not telling. "
"Whatever unspeakable rites they have performed, the result is a beast that "
"knows nothing of its days as a human being, a creature that shambles about "
"as naked as the day it was born, and gorges itself on the flesh of the "
"dead.\n"
"\n"
"It is because of such things that necromancy is condemned with an almost "
"primal hatred.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: A ghoul's claws are covered in poison, and victims of this "
"poison will continually take damage until they can be cured in town or by a "
"healer."
msgstr ""
"只有那些死灵法师知道怎样让人变为食尸鬼，且是不为人知的秘密。无论任何，在那些"
"不为人知的仪式之后，这些生物永远都不再是人。这些至出生起就裸露的生物，以尸体"
"身上的肉为食。\n"
"\n"
"这是死灵法师被人所憎恶的事情之一。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：食尸鬼的爪上有毒，受害者会一直中毒并掉血，知道被治疗或回到村庄。"

#: data/units/Giant_Mudcrawler.cfg:3
msgid "Giant Mudcrawler"
msgstr "巨型黏土怪"

#: data/units/Giant_Mudcrawler.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Giant Mudcrawlers are a larger kind of Mudcrawler, and are magical "
"constructs of soil and water. They attack by belching lumps of mud at their "
"foes, or by slapping them with their fists."
msgstr ""
"巨型黏土怪在黏土怪中占很大的比例，由魔法混合水和泥土制成。他们用吐出的泥块，"
"或拳头进行攻击。"

#: data/units/Giant_Mudcrawler.cfg:50 data/units/Skeleton_Archer.cfg:33
#: data/units/Soulless.cfg:49 data/units/Troll_Rocklobber.cfg:32
#: data/units/Troll_Whelp.cfg:75 data/units/Walking_Corpse.cfg:51
#: data/units/Yeti.cfg:40
msgid "fist"
msgstr "拳头"

#: data/units/Giant_Mudcrawler.cfg:74 data/units/Mudcrawler.cfg:49
msgid "mud glob"
msgstr "黏土攻击"

#: data/units/Giant_Scorpion.cfg:3
msgid "Giant Scorpion"
msgstr "巨型蝎"

#: data/units/Giant_Scorpion.cfg:23
msgid ""
"A normal scorpion is dangerous enough - one the size of a man needs little "
"explanation."
msgstr "一个普通的蝎子就够危险了 － 而如人般巨大的就更不用说。"

#: data/units/Giant_Scorpion.cfg:26
msgid "sting"
msgstr "叮"

#: data/units/Giant_Scorpion.cfg:46
msgid "pincers"
msgstr "钳"

#: data/units/Goblin_Impaler.cfg:4
msgid "Goblin Impaler"
msgstr "地精雇佣兵"

#: data/units/Goblin_Impaler.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Goblins are used by the orcs as fodder for their enemy's front line. Those "
"who have somehow managed to survive invariably equip themselves to continue "
"doing so. A much larger spear helps to compensate for their short reach, and "
"better armor helps to shield their tiny frames.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the length of their weapon allows an impaler to strike first "
"in melee, even in defense."
msgstr ""
"地精常常被兽人用在和敌人作战的前线。这些地精有些让他们能生还下来的装备。一根"
"够长的矛用来弥补他们的不足，不错的铠甲来保护他们瘦小的身躯。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：足够长的武器使得他们在近战中先攻权，防御中也是。"

#: data/units/Goblin_Knight.cfg:3
msgid "Goblin Knight"
msgstr "地精骑士"

#: data/units/Goblin_Knight.cfg:35
msgid ""
"The Goblin 'Knights' have little in common with the men who share that "
"title, and the title is something used only in the parlance of their "
"enemies. The similarity is simply that they are the elite of the wolf "
"riders, likely promoted to their position by their success in some "
"temerarious raid, or something of a similarly base nature.\n"
"\n"
"The wolves they are given are bred for speed and strength, making them quite "
"dangerous in combat."
msgstr ""
"地精‘骑士’这名字有点名不副实，且常常是他们敌人叫的。事实很简单，他们是邪恶狼"
"骑士中的精英，并善于突袭或其它一些天赋而得名。\n"
"\n"
"他们的狼有着极快的速度和强大的力量，使得他们在战斗中十分危险。"

#: data/units/Goblin_Pillager.cfg:3
msgid "Goblin Pillager"
msgstr "地精掠夺者"

#: data/units/Goblin_Pillager.cfg:36
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Some Goblins train their wolves to overcome their fear of fire. In raids, "
"these goblins take a supporting role; they will torch the homes and crops of "
"their foes, and also carry nets to wreak havoc against those attempting to "
"rally a defense or reprisal.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: being caught in a net slows enemies down, halving their "
"movement speed and attack damage."
msgstr ""
"一些地精训练他们的狼不再怕火。在突袭中，这些地精是支援者：他们会烧毁对手的家"
"园，并用网来迫害那些防御或复仇者。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：用网来降低敌人速度，减少他们的攻击次数。"

#: data/units/Goblin_Pillager.cfg:39
msgid "torch"
msgstr "烧毁"

#: data/units/Goblin_Pillager.cfg:57 data/units/Merman_Entangler.cfg:31
#: data/units/Merman_Netcaster.cfg:30
msgid "net"
msgstr "网"

#: data/units/Goblin_Rouser.cfg:3
#, fuzzy
msgid "Goblin Rouser"
msgstr "地精雇佣兵"

#: data/units/Goblin_Rouser.cfg:29
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Standard bearers are an oddity amongst goblins. A goblin who has survived "
"enough battles to be considered a veteran is rare enough, and it is rarer "
"still for the other goblins to recognize and respect his veteran status. "
"Nonetheless, a rouser's frenzied goading effectively steels the younger at "
"arms to fight harder and longer before they die.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the leadership of a Goblin Rouser enables friendly units next "
"to it to deal more damage in combat, though this only applies to units of "
"lower level."
msgstr ""
"高阶元帅级的单位是人类部队里最值得尊敬的一类，拥有这真金不怕火炼的头衔。事实"
"证明他们有个令人自豪的个人战斗经验。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：高阶元帅的领导能力使得相邻的友好单位能造成双倍伤害，但仅适合于低等"
"级。"

#: data/units/Goblin_Spearman.cfg:3
msgid "Goblin Spearman"
msgstr "地精矛战士"

#: data/units/Goblin_Spearman.cfg:24
msgid ""
"In any litter of orcs, several are born much smaller and weaker than the "
"rest. These runts are called 'Goblins' and are looked down on by the rest of "
"their kin. In battle, these are given the most meager of equipment, and are "
"used as a shield to give the Warlords time to prepare the real assault.\n"
"\n"
"Some speculate that the existence of these creatures is the beginning of a "
"failure of the orcish bloodline, though no one knows enough of their history "
"to state anything conclusive."
msgstr ""
"在兽类中很少的一部分，出生时就瘦小和虚弱。这些则被称为‘地精’，并被他们的王所"
"忽略。在战斗中，他们会被给予最差的装备，并作为挡箭牌，来给军阀们足够的时间去"
"对待真正的战斗。\n"
"\n"
"一些人认为这些生物的存在是兽类血液中缺陷的体现，但没人知道详细的历史。"

#: data/units/Grand_Knight.cfg:3
msgid "Grand Knight"
msgstr "大骑兵"

#: data/units/Grand_Knight.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Grand Knights have reached the acme of skill with sword and lance. Wearing "
"full plate, and riding steeds bred more for power than for speed, these "
"warriors form the core of any serious cavalry force. A grand knight at the "
"head of a charge is a terrifying sight for infantry, and is often enough to "
"break right through a defensive line."
msgstr ""
"大骑兵达到了剑和长矛技能的顶峰。全身板甲，并骑着不仅仅急速的战马，这些勇士有"
"着真正骑兵的核心力量。大骑兵是所有步兵所畏惧的，并有强悍的防御线。"

#: data/units/Grand_Knight.cfg:35
msgid ""
"\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the Grand Knight's charging lance attack doubles both damage "
"dealt and received. This does not affect his defensive retaliation."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：大骑兵的长矛攻击有着双倍伤害。在防御是则没有。"

#: data/units/Grand_Knight.cfg:57 data/units/Knight.cfg:56
#: data/units/Lancer.cfg:38 data/units/Paladin.cfg:63
msgid "lance"
msgstr "长矛"

#: data/units/Grand_Marshal.cfg:3
msgid "Grand Marshal"
msgstr "高阶元帅"

#: data/units/Grand_Marshal.cfg:37
msgid ""
"The rank of Grand Marshal is one of the most esteemed in the armies of "
"humanity, and those who bear its title have surpassed many trials by fire, "
"proving their tactical facility and their considerable mettle at personal "
"combat.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the leadership of a Grand Marshal enables friendly units next "
"to it to deal more damage in combat, though this only applies to units of "
"lower level."
msgstr ""
"高阶元帅级的单位是人类部队里最值得尊敬的一类，拥有这真金不怕火炼的头衔。事实"
"证明他们有个令人自豪的个人战斗经验。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：高阶元帅的领导能力使得相邻的友好单位能造成双倍伤害，但仅适合于低等"
"级。"

#: data/units/Great_Mage.cfg:3
msgid "Great Mage"
msgstr "高阶大法师"

#: data/units/Great_Mage.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Any person who is even considered for the title of Great Mage is quite "
"nearly a legend in their own time, and town criers have forcibly learnt "
"discretion in applying the title. Merit for the title is carefully "
"considered by a council of the leading magi of the age, and the conferment "
"of the title is given only by a majority vote. Regardless, anyone who is "
"seriously nominated for the honor of being called a Great Mage is, without "
"question, a master of their art, and has surpassed almost any of their peers "
"in skill.\n"
"\n"
"Though they are not warriors, by any means, the application of their art to "
"combat is something that often causes other soldiers to stand aside in awe.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the great mage's fireballs are magical, and always have a "
"high chance of hitting an opponent."
msgstr ""
"任何人要配的上这个名号需要花费一生的时间来证明，而村庄卫士有权力来辨别他们是"
"否配的上。名号由法师协会的长老来小心谨慎的授予，并且要得到大多投票才能通过。"
"不管任何人被授予这高阶大法师的名号，毋庸置疑，就是魔法大师，并有超于其他法师"
"的易能。\n"
"\n"
"虽然他们不是武士，但他们魔法的攻击性，是让许多战士畏惧的。\n"
"特别提示：高阶大法师的火球是魔法攻击，常常对敌人有很高的击中比率。"

#: data/units/Great_Mage.cfg:110
msgid "female^Great Mage"
msgstr "女性高阶大法师"

#: data/units/Great_Troll.cfg:3
msgid "Great Troll"
msgstr "高阶巨魔"

#: data/units/Great_Troll.cfg:28
msgid ""
"When a troll, gifted with abnormal strength of life, matches that with age "
"and wisdom, it becomes something extraordinary, a beast remembered for "
"generations. Their feats of strength and cunning are the source of most "
"tales about trolls, and to see the stories made flesh does nothing to "
"diminish their grandeur.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Trolls possess the regeneration ability, which heals them as "
"though they were always stationed in a village."
msgstr ""
"当一个巨魔，有着天赋异禀的强大力量，并有合适的年纪和智慧，会非常特别，能够世"
"代相传。这些力量和狡诈的特性是多数巨魔的源力。在那些血腥的故事后，也不会影响"
"他们的庄严。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：巨魔有重新技能，能象他们呆在村庄一样的恢复生命。"

#: data/units/Gryphon.cfg:3
msgid "Gryphon"
msgstr "狮鹫"

#: data/units/Gryphon.cfg:16
msgid ""
"These majestic and powerful creatures are masters of the sky. Gryphons are "
"both dangerous and wary of other intelligent creatures, and thus should not "
"be disturbed without a good reason."
msgstr ""
"这些宏伟和强大的生物是天空的主宰。狮鹫通常很危险且对其它聪明的生物很敏感，所"
"以无事勿扰之。"

#: data/units/Gryphon_Master.cfg:3
msgid "Gryphon Master"
msgstr "狮鹫大师"

#: data/units/Gryphon_Master.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Gryphon Masters have long experience flying the Gryphons, which have become "
"an extension of themselves. This special relationship makes the heart of the "
"earth-bound tremble, for these mighty pairs may strike from anywhere."
msgstr ""
"狮鹫大师很善于利用狮鹫飞行，使之成为自己的扩展。这种特殊的关系也让地界为之颤"
"动，这强大的队伍能从任何方向进行攻击。"

#: data/units/Gryphon_Rider.cfg:3
msgid "Gryphon Rider"
msgstr "狮鹫骑士"

#: data/units/Gryphon_Rider.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Only a few are able to bond with the mighty Gryphons. Those who do may "
"become Gryphon Riders, and discover the world of the skies upon the backs of "
"these flying beasts."
msgstr ""
"仅有少部分能和狮鹫联合起来。这些人就成为狮鹫骑士，并和狮鹫一起去探索天空未知"
"的世界。"

#: data/units/Halbardier.cfg:3
msgid "Halberdier"
msgstr "戟兵"

#: data/units/Halbardier.cfg:31
msgid ""
"A halberd is a difficult and very heavy weapon to use, but powerful in the "
"hands of an expert. It is also much more flexible than the spear from which "
"it descended. As any halberdier can tell you, the weapon possesses 4 primary "
"striking points, 2 more than a spear or pike; these are the tip, the blade, "
"the spike at the base of the shaft, and the inner point on the blade, which "
"can be used in a motion pulling back towards the wielder. All this makes for "
"a very versatile weapon in melee, especially against cavalry.\n"
"\n"
"However, a halberd is notably more expensive to craft than a spear, and in "
"the hands of a novice, much less effective. In the armies of Wesnoth, it is "
"customary only to grant these weapons to veteran pikemen, who have proven "
"that they have the skill to employ them properly on the field of war.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the length of their weapon allows a halberdier to strike "
"first in melee, even in defense."
msgstr ""
"戟兵有着难以使用和笨重的武器，但在行家手里确是强力的。这武器比矛更灵活。戟兵"
"可以自豪的对你说，这武器拥有4个主要打击点，比矛或长矛多2个：是尖刺和刀片，杆"
"上的长钉和刀片内部点，能被用于前后推动挥舞。使得这个武器在战争中变得多样化，"
"特别对骑兵有效。\n"
"\n"
"然而，戟兵没有足够的经验制造武器即使是矛，且作为新手，并不太有效果。在韦诺的"
"军队中，习惯仅仅授予那些武器给经验老练的长矛战士，那些证明在战场上有足够使用"
"他们技能的人。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：这些武器的足够长度使得戟兵有先攻权，即使是在防御中。"

#: data/units/Heavy_Infantryman.cfg:3
msgid "Heavy Infantryman"
msgstr "重甲步兵"

#: data/units/Heavy_Infantryman.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Heavy infantry are an unusual choice for outfitting troops. They are very "
"difficult to send afield in war, and are typically useful only in the "
"defense of the city or castle in which they are stationed. Clad head to toe "
"in full plate, and armed with large maces, heavy infantry excel at their "
"sole purpose of melee combat. A few of them in the center of a line will "
"shore up its strength considerably. The downsides to this are obvious, both "
"in the weight of the metal, and the great care that must be taken of it, but "
"in certain situations, these troops are well worth the trade-offs."
msgstr ""
"重甲步兵是非同寻常的装甲部队。战争离不开他们，并通常用来保卫他们所处的城镇或"
"城堡。装备全身板甲，并装备大型权杖，他们唯一擅长于近战。少量的他们站成一线就"
"能组成强大的队伍。但也有一些明显的缺陷如笨重的铠甲和脱下后得小心照料，但通"
"常，他们是值得训练的。"

#: data/units/Horseman.cfg:3
msgid "Horseman"
msgstr "骑手"

#: data/units/Horseman.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Often hailing from the rather untamed regions of Wesnoth, Horsemen are "
"trained from childhood to ride and to follow a strict code of honor. A "
"charge made by a horseman is a powerful but reckless tactic, the worth of "
"which has been proven time and time again on the battlefield. Horsemen excel "
"against most infantry, especially those who have fallen out of line, but "
"must take care against both spearmen and archers, for whom their large size "
"and momentum provide inviting targets."
msgstr ""
"常常来至于韦诺中不可控区域，骑手从小就受训骑术并遵守极其严格的法典。骑手的冲"
"锋强而有力但确实鲁莽的战术，在战争中一次次被证实为有价值的战术。骑手善于攻击"
"步兵，特别是那些游离于队形之外的，但是要小心应付矛战士和弓箭手，他们高大的身"
"材很容易成为这些人的靶子。"

#: data/units/Horseman.cfg:34
msgid ""
"\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the Horseman's only attack is a charge, which doubles both "
"damage dealt and received. This does not affect his defensive retaliation."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：骑手仅能用冲锋攻击，供认能造成双倍攻击。但在防御时不会。"

#: data/units/Iron_Mauler.cfg:3
msgid "Iron Mauler"
msgstr "铁槌人"

#: data/units/Iron_Mauler.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Iron Maulers are given their name for reasons which are all too obvious. The "
"men within these suits of armor can match ogres in contests of strength, and "
"are marked as the champions of the castle guards in which they serve. They "
"are, however, expensive to maintain, and cannot be sent to distant battles "
"without a full convoy of servants to support them.\n"
"\n"
"Though staggering in melee combat, there are many drawbacks to being "
"outfitted in this way; Iron Maulers tire easily, and know all too well that "
"they cannot run on the battlefield. Too often have they seen a distant "
"comrade fall, yet were powerless to reach the scene in time to help."
msgstr ""
"铁槌人名字的由来非常明显。配置这些装甲的人有着与食人魔匹敌的力量，并是他们所"
"效忠城堡中守卫里面的佼佼者。然而，他们有着昂贵的维护费，而且需要完整的后援支"
"持即使是离开战争。\n"
"\n"
"虽然有着惊人的战斗能力，但也会有缺陷：铁槌人容易疲劳，并且不能在战场上跑动。"
"由于离疏远同伴，而不能有效的进行助救。"

#: data/units/Javelineer.cfg:3
msgid "Javelineer"
msgstr "标枪兵"

#: data/units/Javelineer.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Spearmen almost always equip themselves with a few javelins, to harry, if "
"not kill, enemies at range. Some, however, take to them rather well, finding "
"that they have a natural talent in their use. Javelineers are a valuable "
"asset to an army, being able to supplement their skill in melee combat with "
"an ability to handle distant foes. They can hurl javelins into enemy ranks "
"from a distance, often without retribution, and still hold their ground in "
"melee.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the length of their weapon allows a javelineer to strike "
"first in melee, even in defense."
msgstr ""
"矛兵有时装备标枪，即使杀不死敌人，也会去骚扰。然而，有些却有着使用标枪的天"
"赋。标枪兵是一个很有价值的兵种，他们在近战中能攻击远处的敌人。他们能投掷标枪"
"至远处的敌人，且不惩罚，并仍然占据当前近战中的位置。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：足够长的武器使得他们有先攻权，即使是防御中。"

#: data/units/Knight.cfg:3
msgid "Knight"
msgstr "骑士"

#: data/units/Knight.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Horsemen of skill and discipline are promoted to Knights. Veterans of "
"combat, they have seen the often-fatal results of a failed charge, and have "
"learnt discretion in its use. Knights, therefore, carry swords in their "
"armament, and practice tactics which, although requiring of much more "
"patience, are far safer than a charge. Their lances are still at the ready, "
"however, and growing experience with these weapons is only to their benefit."
msgstr ""
"拥有足够技能和纪律的骑兵能晋级为骑士。充足的战斗经验，常常能够扭转局势，发挥"
"所学知识。骑士擅长使用剑，尽管需要足够耐心去对待，但总比冲动强。他们的长矛也"
"时刻处在准备状态，然而只有适合他们的武器才能一起成长。"

#: data/units/Knight.cfg:34
msgid ""
"\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the Knight's charging lance attack doubles both damage dealt "
"and received. This does not affect his defensive retaliation."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：骑士能用长矛造成双倍伤害，但防御时无效。"

#: data/units/Lancer.cfg:3
msgid "Lancer"
msgstr "矛骑兵"

#: data/units/Lancer.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Lancers are some of the bravest and most feared riders in all of Wesnoth. "
"Clad in minimal armor, they free themselves to ride swiftly, faster than any "
"of their peers. The daring tactics they employ are a double-edged sword, "
"often winning either glory, or a swift death. Lancers excel in hunting down "
"infantrymen who've made the mistake of breaking formation, and in piercing "
"defensive lines. However, they have limited use in defense."
msgstr ""
"矛骑兵是韦诺世界里最勇敢和令人恐惧的骑兵。穿着轻甲，能够迅速移动，比其他同族"
"都快。他们大胆运用在战术中的武器是双刃大剑，常能赢得荣誉或迅速死亡。矛骑兵擅"
"长于击垮那些松散的步兵集团。然而，他们的防御却很有限。"

#: data/units/Lancer.cfg:35
msgid ""
"\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the Lancer's charging lance attack doubles both damage dealt "
"and received. This does not affect his defensive retaliation."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：矛骑兵使用长矛冲锋来造成双倍伤害。但防御是无效。"

#: data/units/Lich.cfg:3
msgid "Lich"
msgstr "巫妖"

#: data/units/Lich.cfg:31
msgid ""
"A lich is the physical embodiment of black magic's first goal: the quest to "
"achieve immortality. Though a great deal is sacrificed in the rebirth, in "
"becoming a lich one cheats death of that which truly gives it terror. For it "
"is the mind that is retained, and the spirit which follows, though the body "
"may wither away.\n"
"\n"
"It is not known, save perhaps by the inner circles of necromancy, whether "
"life is prolonged indefinitely or simply extended. But to even consider such "
"a thing bears tribute to the magnitude of what they have already achieved.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: The ranged attacks of a lich are magical, and always have a "
"high chance of hitting an opponent. The touch of a lich drains the victim's "
"life to renew the lich."
msgstr ""
"巫妖是黑暗魔法的具体化身：完成了不朽之路的探索。虽然为获得重生做出了巨大的牺"
"牲，成为巫妖却是对死亡的欺骗。虽然思想和灵魂依然存在，但身体会腐朽。\n"
"\n"
"未知的是，死灵法术可能会挽救他们的，无论生命无限或简单的延续。但完全肯定的是"
"他们要为他们已经完成的愿望而付出一些东西。\n"
"\n"
"比特提示：巫妖的远程攻击是魔法攻击，并对敌人有很高的击中比率。巫妖之触会让受"
"害人的生命转到他们自己身上。"

#: data/units/Lieutenant.cfg:3
msgid "Lieutenant"
msgstr "中尉"

#: data/units/Lieutenant.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Trained at swords and crossbows, Lieutenants lead small groups of human "
"soldiers, coordinating their attacks.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the leadership of a Lieutenant enables friendly units next to "
"it to deal more damage in combat, though this only applies to units of lower "
"level."
msgstr ""
"受训使用剑和弩，中尉领导一小撮部队，协调他们的攻击。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：中尉的领导能力是的相邻的友好单位能造成双倍攻击，但只对低等级单位有"
"效。"

#: data/units/Longbowman.cfg:3
msgid "Longbowman"
msgstr "长弓手"

#: data/units/Longbowman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Longbows are forbidden to beginning archers simply by merit of physical law. "
"It takes great strength to draw one, and the added range and power are "
"useless unless one has good aim with the weapon, a gift that beginners "
"certainly lack. Longbowmen carry their weaponry as a badge of pride, and "
"most bowmen look forward to the day they can begin using one."
msgstr ""
"长弓在法律上不被允许新手弓箭手使用，需要很大的力气才能拉动，增加射程和力量是"
"无效的除非能够很好的瞄准目标，新手一定不会被给予。长弓手的武器是他们的荣耀，"
"并且大多数弓手一生都在为之追求。"

#: data/units/Mage.cfg:3
msgid "Mage"
msgstr "魔法师"

#: data/units/Mage.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Humans have often pondered the workings of the world in which they live. "
"Some endeavor to take this beyond idle musing, to set it as the primary "
"enterprise of their lives. Magi have spent several years in study, and have "
"amassed a sum of knowledge which sets them apart. In a world where few "
"people can read and write, these men and women have committed themselves "
"fully to the pursuit of knowledge. Their ranks are filled with the children "
"of hopeful nobility, or those who sought an escape from the intellectual "
"void begotten by a life of manual labor.\n"
"\n"
"It is an irony that, with all the knowledge they have amassed and their "
"unassuming monopoly of it, the collective community of magi could likely "
"rule society, were they ever to try. However, their true love is neither "
"money, nor power, and those who see the study of magic as a means to such "
"ends often lack the very conviction that is required for true mastery.\n"
"\n"
"Physically frail, and lacking familiarity with combat, magi do possess "
"certain arts which are of great utility in battle.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the ranged attack of a mage is magical, and always has a high "
"chance of hitting an opponent."
msgstr ""
"人类常常思索这个他们所居住世界的运作方式。一些空闲时间的努力冥想，好似成为他"
"们生命中唯一的事情。魔法师花费许多年时间学习，并学到很多知识而与社会脱节。世"
"界里有少许人能读和写，他(她)们一生都在追求知识。这些知识遗留给下一代，并写入"
"永世不灭的手册中。\n"
"\n"
"讽刺的是，这些他们所积累的知识和不屑的，使得魔法协会能控制社会，就如他们曾经"
"尝试的那样。然而他们的真爱不是钱或力量，这些学习魔法艺术的人却缺乏能成为真正"
"统治者的必须信念。\n"
"\n"
"身体虚弱并且不善于战斗，魔法师仍然有战争中强大的攻击工具。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：魔法师的远程攻击是魔法攻击，并对敌人有很高的击中比率。"

#: data/units/Mage.cfg:78 data/units/Silver_Mage.cfg:111
msgid "missile"
msgstr "魔法飞弹"

#: data/units/Mage.cfg:119
msgid "female^Mage"
msgstr "女性魔法师"

#: data/units/Mage_of_Light.cfg:3
msgid "Mage of Light"
msgstr "光明魔法师"

#: data/units/Mage_of_Light.cfg:41
msgid ""
"After years of experience, the most devout of white magi are bestowed with "
"vast spiritual powers. By strict devotion to the path of the light, they can "
"call upon its aid to chase away the shadows of the night.\n"
"\n"
"Following a strict code of piety and honor, these men and women work "
"tirelessly to bring life and order to the troubled world in which they "
"live.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the light cast by a mage of light is magical in nature, and "
"always has a high chance of hitting an opponent. This light does tremendous "
"damage to the undead, and even does some to living creatures. Magi of Light "
"are capable of healing units around them, and curing them of poison. They "
"also have the power of Illumination, which increases the lighting level in "
"the area adjacent to the mage."
msgstr ""
"多年积累的经验，最虔诚的白袍法师被授予巨大的神圣力量。绝对热爱光明之路，他们"
"能驱散黑暗的阴影。\n"
"\n"
"随着绝对的虔诚和荣誉，他(她)们不知疲倦的带来生命并服务于他们这个混乱的世"
"界。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：光明魔法师的圣力是自然魔法攻击，对敌人有很高的击中比率。圣力对不死"
"有巨大的伤害力，对有些活物也是。光明魔法能治疗相邻单位，并治愈中毒。他们也有"
"照明法术，提高周围的可见度。"

#: data/units/Mage_of_Light.cfg:62 data/units/Mermaid_Diviner.cfg:60
#: data/units/Mermaid_Priestess.cfg:54 data/units/White_Mage.cfg:82
msgid "lightbeam"
msgstr "光线"

#: data/units/Mage_of_Light.cfg:63 data/units/Mermaid_Diviner.cfg:61
#: data/units/Mermaid_Priestess.cfg:55 data/units/Paladin.cfg:46
#: data/units/White_Mage.cfg:83
msgid "holy"
msgstr "神圣"

#: data/units/Mage_of_Light.cfg:95
msgid "female^Mage of Light"
msgstr "女性光明魔法师"

#: data/units/Master_Bowman.cfg:3
msgid "Master Bowman"
msgstr "弓箭手大师"

#: data/units/Master_Bowman.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Master bowmen have reached the zenith of their art, inasmuch as any man is "
"capable. Armed with both a sword, and a great yew bow, these warriors crown "
"battalions of archers with their presence, bringing down many a foe with "
"their well-aimed shots. Their skill with the sword is also not to be "
"discounted; they are easily as good with it as any novice swordsman. Of the "
"many races in the world, only the elves surpass humanity in archery, and "
"their human counterparts have speculated, perhaps in envy, that this is only "
"by dint of age."
msgstr ""
"弓箭手大师有着经典的战斗技艺，因而很多人都合适。装备剑和大紫杉弓，这个勇士以"
"弓箭手部队的精英出现，给予敌人致命的打击。他们剑术技能也丝毫不大折扣：他们很"
"轻松就能比那些新手剑士更好。在这个世界的许多种族，只有精灵有着凌驾于人类之上"
"的箭术技能，那些人类同行推测过，或许是由于嫉妒，说这是由于年龄的原因。"

#: data/units/Master_at_Arms.cfg:3
msgid "Master at Arms"
msgstr "武器大师"

#: data/units/Master_at_Arms.cfg:24
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Master fencers have an envied place in life. Though theirs is a reckless and "
"dangerous way of life, they have reached the time wherein they reap its "
"rewards. Famed for their skill, and their rakish manner, these gentlemen "
"have the bearing of natural aristocrats, and are followed by the eyes of "
"many a high born lady.\n"
"\n"
"They usually have the luxury of choosing their appointments, and are free to "
"roam the land should they so choose. Often, they will be found as the "
"captains of a castle guard, or as the master of a military academy, "
"positions in which their flamboyant nature is not only accepted, but is "
"perhaps even useful.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: their skill at skirmishing allows these master fencers to "
"dart right past an opponent, ignoring zones of control."
msgstr ""
"剑术大师有着令人羡慕的一生。虽然这是刺激和危险的一生，但是在某些方面他们也有"
"所获。以高超的技能和潇洒风度而闻名，这些绅士有着天生贵族的气息，被许多天生贵"
"妇所仰慕。\n"
"\n"
"他们非常在意他们的任务选择，并能在所选的土地上任意遨游。通常，他们作为城堡的"
"守卫首领出现，或军事学院的大师，他们耀眼的地位不仅仅被公认，也十分有用。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：他们侦察的技能允许这个剑术大师能从对手身边轻易通过，并忽略可控制区"
"域。"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Diviner.cfg:3
msgid "female^Mermaid Diviner"
msgstr "女性美人鱼占卜师"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Diviner.cfg:38
msgid ""
"Mermaid Priestesses meet their calling with a fervor that leaves their human "
"counterparts somewhat taken aback. This may have its roots in a legend they "
"recite, telling of a nameless, shadowy horror which was once the bane of "
"their people. Though little is told about it, it is clear that it was the "
"power of the light which somehow defeated it, and made their people safe.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the light cast by a diviner is magical in nature, and always "
"has a high chance of hitting an opponent. This light does tremendous damage "
"to the undead, and even does some to living creatures. Diviners are capable "
"of healing units around them, and curing them of poison. They also have the "
"power of Illumination, which increases the lighting level in the area "
"adjacent to the mermaid."
msgstr ""
"美人鱼女祭司认为这热情的职业与人类同行有些相似。这是有些传说依据的，出于无名"
"氏之口，黑暗，恐怖，是他们子民消失的原因。虽然很少提及，打败敌人的光明力量，"
"并保卫他们的子民是明确的。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：占卜师发出的光明攻击是自然魔法攻击，并对敌人有很高的击中比率。圣力"
"对不死有巨大的伤害力，对有些活物也是。光明魔法能治疗相邻单位，并治愈中毒。他"
"们也有照明法术，提高周围的可见度。"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Enchantress.cfg:3
msgid "female^Mermaid Enchantress"
msgstr "女性美人鱼女巫"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Enchantress.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Mermaids, like elves, have a powerful and native ability in magic, though "
"theirs is considerably different. Those who master this ability are held in "
"high regard, and their skill is used in a multitude of crafts, many of which "
"are things that humanity would never dream of. The obvious use in war is "
"forbidden against their own race - this power is the greater part of what "
"protects their people from the monsters that wander out of the abyss.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: The blasts of water conjured by mermaids are magical in "
"nature, and always have a high chance of hitting their opponents."
msgstr ""
"美人鱼，象精灵一样，有着惊人的强大自然魔法天赋，虽然释放起来有点困难。那些拥"
"有这些能力的大师能获得足够的尊敬，比用于制造许多设备，有些是人类永远不会想到"
"的。战争中严禁对自己族人使用 － 这些力量很大一部分用来保护他们的族人免于被徘"
"徊在地狱之外的怪兽伤害。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：他们释放的水浪攻击是自然魔法攻击，并对敌人有着很高的击中比率。"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Enchantress.cfg:49 data/units/Mermaid_Initiate.cfg:51
#: data/units/Mermaid_Siren.cfg:78
msgid "water spray"
msgstr "水浪"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Initiate.cfg:3
msgid "female^Mermaid Initiate"
msgstr "女性美人鱼传授者"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Initiate.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Young Mermaids are often initiated into the water magics native to their "
"people. The wondrous abilities this grants are inimitable by any other race, "
"a mark of the faerie side of these creatures.\n"
"\n"
"Despite their frailty, this makes them quite formidable in combat, as they "
"can call upon the very water about them to smite their enemies.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the blasts of water conjured by mermaids are magical in "
"nature, and always have a high chance of hitting their opponents."
msgstr ""
"年轻的美人鱼通常被授予水魔法使用的能力。这独一无二的能力是其他种族所无法比拟"
"的，是这些仙境生物的标志。\n"
"\n"
"尽管他们虚弱，这让他们在战斗中十分可怕，能召唤周围的水来攻击敌人。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：他们释放的水浪攻击是自然魔法攻击，并对敌人有着很高的击中比率。"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Priestess.cfg:3
msgid "female^Mermaid Priestess"
msgstr "女性美人鱼女祭司"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Priestess.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Mermen share the creed that much of humanity follows, though for cultural "
"reasons, the upholding of this is left to the mermaids, who are more "
"intellectually inclined. It is they who dedicate themselves to the ideal of "
"bringing peace and life to the world, and they who study the arts of "
"battling sickness and injury, maladies which they share in no small part "
"with humanity. Their diligence and piety also grant them certain spiritual "
"powers, allowing them to guard their people against the unworldly.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the light cast by a priestess is magical in nature, and "
"always has a high chance of hitting an opponent. This light does tremendous "
"damage to the undead, and even does some to living creatures. Priestesses "
"are capable of healing units around them, and curing them of poison."
msgstr ""
"美人鱼有着象人类一样的宗教信仰，虽然由于文化的原因，坚持信仰的美人鱼，都有知"
"识分子的头脑。他们有着寻求和平与生命的理念。他们学习战胜疾病和伤害，女祭司有"
"着无私和博爱的胸怀。他们的勤奋和虔诚给予他们神圣能力，允许他们用来保护族"
"人。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：他们发出的光明攻击是自然魔法攻击，并对敌人有很高的击中比率。圣力对"
"不死有巨大的伤害力，对有些活物也是。光明魔法能治疗相邻单位，并治愈中毒。"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Siren.cfg:3
msgid "Siren"
msgstr "海妖"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Siren.cfg:30
msgid ""
"The faerie nature of the mermaids is strongest in the Sirens, whose "
"connection to naia often causes them to be mistaken for naiads themselves. "
"Though certainly far from the truth, the mistake is understandable, as true "
"naiads are rarely seen even by mermaids. The manifestation of their magic is "
"certainly very similar; the water about a siren can be commanded at whim, "
"like an extension of herself.\n"
"\n"
"The myriad applications of this rarely occur to land dwellers, who simply "
"regard it with wonder.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the attacks of a siren are magical in nature, and always have "
"a high chance of hitting their opponents."
msgstr ""
"美人鱼海妖是海妖中最强壮的，常常与水中仙子有联系使的他们可能成为水中仙子们自"
"己的错误。虽然远离真象，但这个错误是可以理解的，美人鱼们也能难看到水中仙子。"
"他们的魔法被证实非常简单：海妖能用意念操纵水，就像他们自己的一部分。\n"
"\n"
"无数事件证实了他们有极少数成为陆地居民，常常由于他们的怪模样而被关注。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：海妖的攻击是自然魔法攻击，并对敌人有很高的击中比率。"

#: data/units/Mermaid_Siren.cfg:34
msgid "naia touch"
msgstr "水中仙子之触"

#: data/units/Merman_Entangler.cfg:3
msgid "Merman Entangler"
msgstr "男性鱼人缠绕者"

#: data/units/Merman_Entangler.cfg:20
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The weighted nets used by mermen in warfare are a difficult weapon to use "
"well; those who master it are valued and revered by their comrades. This "
"weapon helps to cement the utter superiority of a merman in his own element, "
"and makes their race a threat even to enemies who merely approach the "
"water.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: being caught in a net slows enemies down, halving their "
"movement speed and attack damage."
msgstr ""
"被男性鱼人使用的重网是件很难用好的武器：那些大师受同伴尊敬和崇拜。这件武器附"
"着于男性鱼人全身，并又来阻止敌人进入他们的领地。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：被网住的敌人会减速并减慢攻击频率。"

#: data/units/Merman_Fighter.cfg:3
msgid "Merman Fighter"
msgstr "男性鱼人战士"

#: data/units/Merman_Fighter.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Skilled creatures of the sea, Mermen are powerful and quick in any watery "
"environment, but struggle greatly to move on land."
msgstr "海中富有技能的生物。鱼人在任何水中都是快速和强力的，但在陆地上则相反。"

#: data/units/Merman_Fighter.cfg:30 data/units/Merman_Hoplite.cfg:46
#: data/units/Merman_Triton.cfg:31 data/units/Merman_Triton.cfg:45
#: data/units/Merman_Warrior.cfg:30
msgid "trident"
msgstr "三叉戟"

#: data/units/Merman_Hoplite.cfg:3
msgid "Merman Hoplite"
msgstr "男性鱼人重甲步兵"

#: data/units/Merman_Hoplite.cfg:43
msgid ""
"With their towering shields, the Merman Hoplites form the elite guard of the "
"watery realm. Their powerful armor and rigid discipline allow them to hold a "
"steadfast line against the rages of battle. In times of desperation, they "
"can even do so on land, though not nearly as well as a creature with legs."
msgstr ""
"有着高耸的盾牌，来至于水世界里守卫中的精英。强力的铠甲和严厉的军纪使得他们在"
"狂暴的战争中能组织严密的战线。在绝望之间，他们依然能在陆地上有所作为，多然不"
"太接近那些有腿的生物。"

#: data/units/Merman_Hunter.cfg:3
msgid "Merman Hunter"
msgstr "男性鱼人猎手"

#: data/units/Merman_Hunter.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The skills employed by mermen in spear-fishing are easily translated into "
"warfare, especially against those who are not at home in the water. In times "
"of need, many mermen of that occupation will volunteer to swell the ranks of "
"their military."
msgstr ""
"鱼人用矛捕鱼的技能被转换到战争中，特别是对那些非水中生物的敌人。由于很需这些"
"职业，许多鱼人志愿加入这种级别的军队。"

#: data/units/Merman_Javelineer.cfg:3
msgid "Merman Javelineer"
msgstr "男性鱼人标枪兵"

#: data/units/Merman_Javelineer.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Those mermen who master the art of javelinry can become nearly as effective "
"as an archer - though the heft of their weapons impedes their range, the "
"impact of one is considerably greater. In the water, the mobility of the "
"mermen more than makes up for this when facing foes who cannot swim."
msgstr ""
"这些投掷标枪的大师级鱼人与弓箭手一样有效 － 虽然他们武器的影响阻碍了他们的射"
"程，且是非常大的影响。在水中，这些鱼人的机动性非常号，特别是当面对那些不能游"
"泳的敌人时。"

#: data/units/Merman_Netcaster.cfg:3
msgid "Merman Netcaster"
msgstr "男性鱼人网投手"

#: data/units/Merman_Netcaster.cfg:19
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Fishing, as practiced by mermen, is largely a matter of chasing schools of "
"fish into waiting nets. These are not very damaging in themselves, but they "
"can be used to great effect against troops attempting to ford a river. "
"Smaller, weighted nets can be cast through the air; though these are not "
"designed for peacetime use, they are especially effective in warfare. Mermen "
"use such weapons both to immobilize troops in water, and more importantly, "
"to level the playing field against troops on land, who would otherwise be at "
"a great advantage.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: being caught in a net slows enemies down, halving their "
"movement speed and attack damage."
msgstr ""
"捕鱼，是鱼人在学校里进一步学习用网技能的前提。这并不会伤害他们自己，但曾经用"
"于与在浅滩的部队作战。小型网能向空中撒去：虽然不是用于在和平时期使用，在战争"
"中却很有效。鱼人用这些武器固定部队，并且是非常重要的。也敌人在陆地上作战，这"
"些也是很有优势的。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：被网住的部队会收到减速影响并降低击中比率。"

#: data/units/Merman_Spearman.cfg:3
msgid "Merman Spearman"
msgstr "鱼人矛兵"

#: data/units/Merman_Spearman.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Archery is little favored by the mermen, for whom javelinry serves the same "
"function. Though thrown javelins are of little use under the water, they are "
"extremely useful at the surface, where their weight allows them to plunge "
"several feet below the water while retaining enough momentum to remain "
"effective. They are also useful in melee, even deep under the surface, which "
"is something that certainly cannot be said of arrows."
msgstr ""
"鱼人不太爱使用箭术，投掷标枪也一样。虽然投掷标枪在水下用的很少，但在水面以上"
"却非常有效，他们的负重会减低少许移动力但仍然有足够的战斗能力。他们在近战中也"
"很有用，即使在很深的水面以下，那些一定不适合箭的地方。"

#: data/units/Merman_Triton.cfg:3
msgid "Merman Triton"
msgstr "鱼人三叉戟士兵"

#: data/units/Merman_Triton.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Tritons are masters of the sea. Skilled in use of the trident, Tritons "
"easily defeat any enemy foolish enough to wander into their preferred "
"environment."
msgstr ""
"这些是海洋里的大师，擅长于使用三叉戟，他们能很容易的在所熟悉的环境里愚弄敌"
"人。"

#: data/units/Merman_Warrior.cfg:3
msgid "Merman Warrior"
msgstr "鱼人勇士"

#: data/units/Merman_Warrior.cfg:27
msgid ""
"The Mermen Warriors form the core of the mermen armies. Wielding powerful "
"tridents, they are a bane to any who dare enter their waters."
msgstr ""
"他们是鱼人部队的精英。有着强力的三叉戟武器，他们是那些胆敢挑战水下世界人们的"
"噩梦。"

#: data/units/Mudcrawler.cfg:3
msgid "Mudcrawler"
msgstr "黏土怪"

#: data/units/Mudcrawler.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Mudcrawlers are magical constructs of soil and water. They attack by "
"belching lumps of mud at their foes."
msgstr "黏土怪由魔法混合水和泥土而成。他们用吐出的黏土攻击敌人。"

#: data/units/Naga-Fighter.cfg:3
msgid "Naga Fighter"
msgstr "娜迦战士"

#: data/units/Naga-Fighter.cfg:25
msgid ""
"The serpentine naga are one of the few races capable of any meaningful "
"mobility in water, giving them a whole world forbidden to land dwellers. "
"Still, they are not true creatures of the sea, and their inability to "
"breathe water leaves them in trepidation of the abyss. They are small, and "
"somewhat frail in form, but often much more nimble than their opponents."
msgstr ""
"蛇型娜迦是水中有着非凡能力的少数一族，被给予一个远离陆地居民的世界。然而，他"
"们并非真正的海洋生物，他们不能在深海进行长久有效的呼吸。他们小巧而虚弱，但常"
"常比敌人更灵活。"

#: data/units/Naga-Fighter.cfg:47
msgid "Nagini Fighter"
msgstr "娜迦战士"

#: data/units/Naga-Myrmidon.cfg:3
msgid "Naga Myrmidon"
msgstr "娜迦跟班"

#: data/units/Naga-Myrmidon.cfg:30
msgid ""
"The most practiced of the naga blademasters are initiated into the caste of "
"the Myrmidon, masters of their twin-bladed art. They strike as fast as the "
"snakes which they resemble, and dance away from attacks with grace. Not only "
"are they potent enemies on any open terrain, but their ability to swim "
"allows them a deadly mobility."
msgstr ""
"大多数的娜迦剑术大师成为集团的跟班，他们有双刀技能。他们有着如蛇般的攻击速"
"度，并能以优雅的舞步离开战斗。不仅能在许多开阔的地形上进行攻击，而且他们的游"
"泳能力给予他们致命的机动性。"

#: data/units/Naga-Myrmidon.cfg:52
msgid "Nagini Myrmidon"
msgstr "娜迦跟班"

#: data/units/Naga-Myrmidon.cfg:55
msgid ""
"The most practiced of the nagini blademasters are initiated into the caste "
"of the Myrmidon, masters of their twin-bladed art. They strike as fast as "
"the snakes which they resemble, and dance away from attacks with grace. Not "
"only are they potent enemies on any open terrain, but their ability to swim "
"allows them a deadly mobility."
msgstr ""
"大多数的娜迦剑术大师成为集团的跟班，他们有双刀技能。他们有着如蛇般的攻击速"
"度，并能以优雅的舞步离开战斗。不仅能在许多开阔的地形上进行攻击，而且他们的游"
"泳能力给予他们致命的机动性。"

#: data/units/Naga-Warrior.cfg:3
msgid "Naga Warrior"
msgstr "娜迦勇士"

#: data/units/Naga-Warrior.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Many of the young warriors of the naga aspire for the day when they merit "
"their second blade. Their martial practice of using twin blades is wholly "
"unlike that of the Orcs and other races, for they have begun to learn the "
"art of using their serpentine form to best effect, twisting and turning to "
"dodge from blows. This makes them potent on land, but the friction of water "
"greatly impedes their ability to do this."
msgstr ""
"大多年轻的娜迦勇士渴望有一天能得到他们的另一把剑。他们在战场上使用双剑的能力"
"完全不同于兽人或其他种族，他们一直在练习如何运用蛇型的身体进行有效的攻击，扭"
"转和跳跃打击。这些使得他们在陆地上很强大，但在水中却无所作为。"

#: data/units/Naga-Warrior.cfg:51
msgid "Nagini Warrior"
msgstr "娜迦勇士"

#: data/units/Necromancer.cfg:3
msgid "Necromancer"
msgstr "死灵法师"

#: data/units/Necromancer.cfg:25
msgid ""
"One of the greatest circles of what is considered 'black magic' is the art "
"of necromancy, the terrible ability to awaken the dead with false life. This "
"ability, in all aspects, was the first step towards cheating death of its "
"ultimate prize; though not the fulfillment of what they had hoped for, it "
"was a discovery that nonetheless had terrible ramifications. This art alone "
"may have caused humanity's condemnation of what is now known as 'black "
"magic', and has given fear a vast new arsenal.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: The ranged attacks of a necromancer are magical, and always "
"have a high chance of hitting an opponent."
msgstr ""
"死灵法师有着最强大的使用‘黑暗魔法’能力，这可怕的能力能唤醒死去的灵魂。这能"
"力，完全是伴随着极大代价，对死亡的欺骗：虽然并非称心如意，也是对可怕能力的探"
"索。这被人人唾弃的‘黑暗魔法’却能造出令人恐惧的军队。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：死灵法师的攻击是魔法攻击，并对敌人有很高的击中比率。"

#: data/units/Necrophage.cfg:3
msgid "Necrophage"
msgstr "死灵食尸鬼"

#: data/units/Necrophage.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Driven ravenous by an unholy hunger for dead flesh, Necrophages attack their "
"hoped-for food with beast-like ferocity. When they are sated with the flesh "
"of their victims, they simply shrug off all damage sustained as if they had "
"been freshly summoned, to begin their search for flesh again.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: A Necrophage's claws are covered in poison, and victims of "
"this poison will continually take damage until they can be cured in town or "
"by a healer."
msgstr ""
"对腐肉有着极大的嗜好，他们对想象中的食物进行凶狠的攻击。当他们食用受害者的腐"
"肉之后，就会毫发无伤，就像刚刚召唤出来一样。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：死灵食尸鬼的爪有毒，能使敌人持续掉血，知道进入村庄或被治愈。"

#: data/units/Nightgaunt.cfg:3
msgid "Nightgaunt"
msgstr "夜幕刺客"

#: data/units/Nightgaunt.cfg:25
msgid ""
"The purpose of the masks that these creatures wear is unknown, as is the "
"countenance that they obscure. These terrible forms are rarely seen by the "
"living, and those who live to speak of them had no leisure to study their "
"foe.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: while a unit with the same allegiance as the nightgaunt "
"distracts an enemy, the nightgaunt may strike at the opponent's back, "
"inflicting double damage. Nightgaunts have very unusual resistances to "
"damage, and move quite slowly over open water. Nightgaunts are able to hide "
"at night, leaving no trace of their presence."
msgstr ""
"这些生物出现的意图不为人所知，正如他们的阴暗面容一样。这些恐怖生物形式极少"
"见，面对他们时很难存活。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：当面对一个敌人时，他们会从后面进行攻击，造成双倍伤害。他们对伤害有"
"非凡的抗性，并且在水面上移动的十分缓慢。他们能在夜幕中隐藏，隐匿行踪。"

#: data/units/Ogre.cfg:3
msgid "Ogre"
msgstr "食人魔"

#: data/units/Ogre.cfg:23
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Ogres are giant creatures that usually live alone in the wilderness, "
"remarkably similar to humans in form, though large and misshapen. While they "
"can be easily outrun or outsmarted, their strength is not to be "
"underestimated."
msgstr ""
"食人魔常常是单独生活在野外的巨大生物，长的非常像人类，虽然巨大和丑陋。虽然有"
"可能轻易打败他们，但他们的力量是不可忽视的。"

#: data/units/Ogre.cfg:26 data/units/Young_Ogre.cfg:47
msgid "cleaver"
msgstr "切割"

#: data/units/Orcish_Archer.cfg:3
msgid "Orcish Archer"
msgstr "兽人弓箭手"

#: data/units/Orcish_Archer.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Orcish Archers are considered by many of their fellow orcs to be a lesser "
"caste of warrior, for attacking their enemies from a distance. However, "
"since most orcs won't learn how to handle a bow, he is an indispensable part "
"of the orcish army."
msgstr ""
"兽人弓箭手是仅次于勇士被本族所尊敬的，能在远距离进行攻击。然而，很少有兽人受"
"训于箭术，他们是兽人军队不可或缺的一部分。"

#: data/units/Orcish_Assassin.cfg:3
msgid "Orcish Assassin"
msgstr "兽人暗杀者"

#: data/units/Orcish_Assassin.cfg:25
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Though some consider it cowardly to use, poison is a weapon favored by orcs, "
"especially those weak of frame. Orcish assassins, who use it on throwing "
"knives, are typically a bit frail, although surprisingly nimble. Though "
"rarely the ones who deal the killing blow, their tactics are a considerable "
"aid to their larger and more brutal kin.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Orcish Assassins use poison on their throwing knives, and "
"victims of this poison will continually take damage until they can be cured "
"in town or by a healer."
msgstr ""
"虽考虑到很少被使用，但毒武器是却兽人的最爱 － 特别对于这些虚弱的体格，兽人暗"
"杀者用在飞刀上，攻击力很低，虽然有着惊人的速度。虽然极少能进行强有力的攻击，"
"但他们的战术却受到大量同类的赞许。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：兽人暗杀者使用涂毒飞刀，并使敌人不停损失生命直到进入村庄或被治愈。"

#: data/units/Orcish_Assassin.cfg:47 data/units/Orcish_Slayer.cfg:53
msgid "throwing knives"
msgstr "飞刀"

#: data/units/Orcish_Crossbowman.cfg:3
msgid "Orcish Crossbowman"
msgstr "兽人弩手"

#: data/units/Orcish_Crossbowman.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Orcish Crossbowmen try to compensate for their lack of skill with the raw "
"power of their weapon. While they are not as effective as the Elvish "
"Marksmen in long-range combat, they are sturdier and can handle themselves a "
"little better than the Elves in close combat."
msgstr ""
"兽人弩手用这强力锋利的武器来弥补他们的不足。虽然不如精灵神射手那样在长距离战"
"斗中那样有效，但他们却在近战中强于精灵们。"

#: data/units/Orcish_Crossbowman.cfg:26 data/units/Orcish_Slurbow.cfg:27
msgid "short sword"
msgstr "短剑"

#: data/units/Orcish_Grunt.cfg:3
msgid "Orcish Grunt"
msgstr "咕噜兽"

#: data/units/Orcish_Grunt.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Orcish Grunts form the core of the orcish forces. Although slower than human "
"or elven fighters, Grunts can deliver much more powerful blows, and take "
"more hits before falling."
msgstr ""
"咕噜兽是兽人的中坚力量。虽然慢于人类或精灵战士，他们却能造成巨大的打击伤害，"
"并能在造成多次打击。"

#: data/units/Orcish_Slayer.cfg:3
msgid "Orcish Slayer"
msgstr "兽人杀手"

#: data/units/Orcish_Slayer.cfg:26
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The larger, and often more skilled orcish assassins are called 'Slayers' by "
"their enemies, though this distinction is somewhat unclear. Slayers are fast "
"on their feet, and quite nimble in combat, although they achieve that end by "
"forgoing armor. Their weapon of choice, poison, is a vicious tool, and its "
"common use on the battlefield is often the real cause of orcish supremacy.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Orcish Slayers use poison on their throwing knives, and "
"victims of this poison will continually take damage until they can be cured "
"in town or by a healer."
msgstr ""
"大量并有着更强技能的兽人暗杀者被敌人称之为‘兽人杀手’，虽然这些区别并不明显。"
"杀手能快速移动，并在战斗中很灵活，虽然是以失去防御来换嘚得的。他们选择的武器"
"是，涂毒武器，有点残忍，然而确实兽人在战场中的优势所在。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：兽人暗杀者使用涂毒飞刀，并使敌人不停损失生命直到进入村庄或被治愈。"

#: data/units/Orcish_Slurbow.cfg:3
msgid "Orcish Slurbow"
msgstr "兽人投弓手"

#: data/units/Orcish_Slurbow.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Slurbowmen have managed to improve their crossbow with the addition of a "
"cranequin and a metal barrel. As a result they are able to launch lead shot "
"with deadly power and accuracy. Although they remain weaker in ranged combat "
"than their Elven and Human counterparts, they still maintain an edge in "
"melee strength and stamina."
msgstr ""
"投弓手用起重设备和金属桶来改进弩弓。结果使得他们能造成精准的致命一击。虽然仍"
"然在远程战斗中逊色于人类和精灵同行，他们在近战中还是有很强的力量和活力。"

#: data/units/Orcish_Warlord.cfg:3
msgid "Orcish Warlord"
msgstr "兽人军阀"

#: data/units/Orcish_Warlord.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Only orcs with both great cunning and unsurpassed strength can become "
"Warlords. Masters of the sword, and even possessing some skill with the bow, "
"these beast-warriors lead their brethren with an iron hand."
msgstr ""
"仅有那些足够狡诈和非凡力量的兽人能称为军阀。剑术大师和一些箭术技能，这些攻击"
"勇士有着能领导同族兄弟的铁腕能力。"

#: data/units/Orcish_Warrior.cfg:3
msgid "Orcish Warrior"
msgstr "兽人勇士"

#: data/units/Orcish_Warrior.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Having mastered the art of dual-sword fighting, Orcish Warriors are highly "
"respected among the Orcs, and highly feared by their foes. Their only "
"weakness is their inability to wield the bow."
msgstr ""
"有着双重剑大师的战斗技能。兽人勇士倍受尊敬，并使敌人惧怕。他们唯一不强的地方"
"是他们不能装备弓。"

#: data/units/Outlaw.cfg:3
msgid "Outlaw"
msgstr "亡命之徒"

#: data/units/Outlaw.cfg:24
msgid ""
"After some years of service, former 'footpads' rise up in the ranks of their "
"fellow outlaws. Having proven themselves in combat, they are given more "
"dangerous tasks, and a greater share of the spoils. Though many opponents "
"would mock their choice of weaponry, the outlaws are well aware of its "
"deadly capacity, and also of the ready availability of ammunition. Outlaws "
"are somewhat ill at ease fighting during the day, preferring the cover of "
"nightfall."
msgstr ""
"许多年的服务之后，‘拦路强盗’升级为‘亡命之徒’。为证明他们在战斗中的价值，他们"
"被授予更多危险的任务，并能享有一大部分赃物。虽然许多对手嘲笑他们的武器装备，"
"但他们能造成致命打击，也成为有效的军事力量。亡命之徒不善于白天作战，跟喜欢在"
"夜幕掩护之下。"

#: data/units/Outlaw.cfg:85
msgid "female^Outlaw"
msgstr "女性亡命之徒"

#: data/units/Paladin.cfg:3
msgid "Paladin"
msgstr "圣骑士"

#: data/units/Paladin.cfg:39
msgid ""
"Knights of the highest virtue, Paladins have sworn themselves to monastic "
"orders, pledging their might to the cause of righteousness. Though not as "
"imposing on the battlefield as a Grand Knight, a Paladin is a powerful force "
"in combat, and their piety grants them other gifts. A Paladin is a bane to "
"the unworldly, and has trained in ministering to the wounds of his comrades."
msgstr ""
"有着最高美德的骑士，圣骑士成为寺院神职人士，他们是正义的化身。虽然没有大骑兵"
"在战场上那样威风，但圣骑士也是很猛的，他们有着特别的天赋。圣骑士是非尘世间生"
"物的克星，并被训练成能为治疗盟友。"

#: data/units/Paladin.cfg:41
msgid ""
"\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the Paladin's charging lance attack doubles both damage dealt "
"and received. This does not affect his defensive retaliation. The Paladin's "
"holy attack with his sword deals tremendous damage to the undead, and even "
"some to living creatures. Paladins are capable of some healing, though they "
"can only delay the effects of poison, not cure them entirely."
msgstr ""
"\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：圣骑士的长矛能造成双倍伤害，但在防御时无效。圣骑士用剑的神圣攻击能"
"对不死造成巨大伤害，有时对生者也是。他们有治疗能力，虽然他们仅仅能延迟中毒效"
"果，但不能治愈他们。"

#: data/units/Peasant.cfg:3
msgid "Peasant"
msgstr "农夫"

#: data/units/Peasant.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Peasants are the backbone of the rural economy, and the soldiers of last "
"resort. While not fearsome by nature, they will stubbornly defend their "
"homes. However, if you're hurling peasants at your foes, you're clearly out "
"of superior forces."
msgstr ""
"农夫是农村的经济命脉，是最后防线的士兵。虽然并非天生强力，他们仍然顽固的保护"
"他们的家园。然而，如果你把他们当作敌人，你肯定占不到便宜。"

#: data/units/Peasant.cfg:27 data/units/Peasant.cfg:42
msgid "pitchfork"
msgstr "干草叉"

#: data/units/Pikeman.cfg:3
msgid "Pikeman"
msgstr "长矛兵"

#: data/units/Pikeman.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Promising spearmen in the armies of Wesnoth are often graduated to wielding "
"pikes, and are outfitted with something far superior to the motley "
"collection of leather armor they wore as recruits. A pike is a much longer "
"weapon than a spear, and thus facilitates different combat tactics. A wall "
"of pikemen is the bane of any cavalry charge, and with proper discipline and "
"tactics, pikemen can also hold most infantry at bay.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the length of their weapon allows a pikeman to strike first "
"in melee, even in defense."
msgstr ""
"有前途的矛兵通常会晋级为长矛兵，并在刚征募时装备杂色的领袖铠甲。长矛比普通矛"
"要长，因此有不同的战术。长矛兵墙是任何骑兵的噩梦，有着严厉的军纪和战术，长矛"
"兵也能对抗大多数步兵团。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：长矛兵的武器让他们在近战中有先攻权，即使是在防御中。"

#: data/units/Pikeman.cfg:58
msgid "pike"
msgstr "长矛"

#: data/units/Pirate_Galleon.cfg:3
msgid "Pirate Galleon"
msgstr "海盗大帆船"

#: data/units/Pirate_Galleon.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Pirate galleons are to transport ships what wolves are to sheep. Ships full "
"of goods shouldn't be lonely, far away from any land, better to help them to "
"avoid it being sunk from overloading..."
msgstr ""
"海盗大帆船是运输船，上面载着‘披着羊皮的狼’。船只不应该满载货物并独自远离海"
"岸。最好得帮助他们以避免超载(~~!)..."

#: data/units/Poacher.cfg:3
msgid "Poacher"
msgstr "偷猎者"

#: data/units/Poacher.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Poachers rely on their hunting experience and are most valuable at night and "
"in forests and swamps."
msgstr "偷猎者依赖于他们的守猎技能，并喜欢晚上在森林和沼泽作战。"

#: data/units/Red_Mage.cfg:3
msgid "Red Mage"
msgstr "红魔法师"

#: data/units/Red_Mage.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Upon the successful termination of their apprenticeship, a mage is stripped "
"of the blue robes of an apprentice, and given the red robes of a master. The "
"significance of this change is often lost on the peasantry, who mistakenly "
"title Master Magi as 'Red Magi'. Likewise, the symbolism of the change in "
"colors is often mistaken to signify the mage's ability to seemingly conjure "
"fire from nothing but thin air, a trick which, although undeniably useful, "
"is viewed as a crass application of the knowledge which they have "
"painstakingly accrued.\n"
"\n"
"Though physically frail, and untrained as warriors, the 'Red Magi' have a "
"number of tricks up their sleeves, including the gouts of fire which may "
"have cemented their colloquial name.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the red mage's fireballs are magical, and always have a high "
"chance of hitting an opponent."
msgstr ""
"随着新手生涯的终结，新手魔法师脱掉蓝色长袍，并被给予红色大师长袍。这些转换的"
"标志常常是农民迷惑，错误的理解大师头衔如‘红魔法师’。同样的，颜色转变的标志是"
"人们常常认为他们只是有火焰魔法能力的，习惯性的，虽然这些标识不太有用，但人们"
"都会认为这是知识的象征。\n"
"\n"
"虽然身体薄弱，并没被训练成勇士，‘红魔法师’用袖子施展出许多幻术，包括如火焰魔"
"法这适合他们那口语化名字的法术。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：红魔法师的火球攻击是魔法攻击，并对敌人有很高的魔法伤害。"

#: data/units/Red_Mage.cfg:132
msgid "female^Red Mage"
msgstr "女性红魔法师"

#: data/units/Revenant.cfg:3
msgid "Revenant"
msgstr "亡魂"

#: data/units/Revenant.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Given false life to do battle once more, the creatures known as Revenants "
"were clearly great warriors in their time, though the memory of that time is "
"now long gone. Even the sorcerers who raised them can only speculate on "
"their past. Such questions aside, a Revenant is a powerful tool in combat: a "
"fearless warrior that feels no pain, and which will fight to the bitter end."
msgstr ""
"被给予虚假的生命用于战斗，这些生物被称为亡魂。曾经是伟大的勇士，虽然这些记忆"
"以不复存在。甚至那些召唤他们出来的术士也仅仅能推测他们的过去。无需多言，亡魂"
"是强力的战斗工具：无畏的勇士感觉不到疼痛，并战斗至痛苦的重点。"

#: data/units/Rogue.cfg:3
msgid "Rogue"
msgstr "盗贼"

#: data/units/Rogue.cfg:28
msgid ""
"The ringleaders of any group of thieves earn their positions by skill. These "
"rogues have spent many an unpleasant moment darting through crowds and "
"dodging away from those who wish them ill, a set of skills which is very "
"handy in a fight. Masters of knifework, they can also throw knives with "
"reliable accuracy, and their long hours of prowling around at night leave "
"them more comfortable fighting in the dark.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: while a unit with the same allegiance as the rogue distracts "
"an enemy, the rogue may backstab, inflicting double damage, by creeping "
"around behind that enemy."
msgstr ""
"任何小偷组织头目的地位都是由他们的技能所得。这些盗贼当通过和跑开那些希望他们"
"得疾病的人身边时让这些人很不愉快，他们有着非常灵敏的战斗技巧。刀类武器的大"
"师，并能用飞刀进行精准的攻击，长时间在夜晚潜行使得他们更适合在黑暗中战斗。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：当敌人把盗贼的盟友作为攻击目标是，他们能绕到敌人背后，进行背刺，造"
"成双倍打击伤害。"

#: data/units/Rogue.cfg:77
msgid "female^Rogue"
msgstr "女性盗贼"

#: data/units/Royal_Guard.cfg:3
msgid "Royal Guard"
msgstr "皇室守卫者"

#: data/units/Royal_Guard.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Royal Guards are picked from the best swordsmen in Wesnoth. Serving under "
"any of the higher nobility, they function as bodyguards, and partly as a "
"badge of office for their employers. A special force of Royal Guards is "
"stationed at the capitol, guarding the palace grounds and the royal family. "
"Because of their trusted relationship to their superiors, they, rather than "
"mercenaries, are often deployed on missions of crucial import. Their "
"reliability and mastery of close combat are their best assets, for which "
"they are well-renowned."
msgstr ""
"皇室守卫者从韦诺最好的剑士中选出。有着很高的天赋来服务于皇室，他们的职务是保"
"镖，并是部分皇室的象征。他们的特能是驻扎在国会大厦，保护这片地方和皇室成员。"
"因为他们获得上级的足够信任，不想雇佣兵那样，他们常常被给予非常机密重要的任"
"务。他们强而有力有利的近战技能是他们的资本，也是他们知名的地方。"

#: data/units/Saurian_Ambusher.cfg:3
msgid "Saurian Ambusher"
msgstr "蜥蜴人伏兵"

#: data/units/Saurian_Ambusher.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Saurian Ambushers are highly skilled in the use of the spear. Despite their "
"lethargic cold blooded heritage, and their relative frailty, they are highly "
"valued as scouts as they can navigate through rough terrain and around "
"opponents. Saurian Ambushers possess the strength to take full advantage of "
"this fact. The best Ambushers go on to become Saurian Flankers."
msgstr ""
"蜥蜴人伏兵善于用矛作武器。尽管他们天生冷血，也有他们亲戚的弱点。他们很适合作"
"为侦察兵，正如他们有着粗糙地形上的优势。他们拥有这些事实上的优势。最强的蜥蜴"
"人伏兵能成为蜥蜴人侧兵。"

#: data/units/Saurian_Flanker.cfg:4
msgid "Saurian Flanker"
msgstr "蜥蜴人侧兵"

#: data/units/Saurian_Flanker.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Saurian Flankers are highly skilled in the use of the spear. Despite their "
"lethargic cold blooded heritage, and their relative frailty, they are highly "
"valued as scouts as they can navigate through rough terrain and around "
"opponents. Saurian Flankers possess the strength to take full advantage of "
"this fact."
msgstr ""
"蜥蜴人侧兵善于用矛作武器。尽管他们天生冷血，也有他们亲戚的弱点。他们很适合作"
"为侦察兵，正如他们有着粗糙地形上的优势。他们拥有这些事实上的优势。"

#: data/units/Saurian_Icecaster.cfg:3
msgid "Saurian Icecaster"
msgstr "蜥蜴人冰投手"

#: data/units/Saurian_Icecaster.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Saurian Icecasters have eschewed any further training in healing and curing "
"in order to refine their skills with the dark arts. While frail, they can "
"call forth the magic of the cold north, and the do retain their basic "
"healing ability."
msgstr ""
"蜥蜴人冰投手避开任何学习治疗和治愈的技能，是为了学习黑暗力量。虽然虚弱，他们"
"却能使用北方最冷的魔法，也保留了一点治疗能力。"

#: data/units/Saurian_Icecaster.cfg:51 data/units/Saurian_Soothsayer.cfg:51
#: data/units/Saurian_Tribalist.cfg:50
msgid "frost blast"
msgstr "霜冻轰炸"

#: data/units/Saurian_Skirmisher.cfg:3
msgid "Saurian Skirmisher"
msgstr "蜥蜴人刺客"

#: data/units/Saurian_Skirmisher.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Saurian Skirmishers are skilled in the use of the spear. Despite their "
"lethargic cold blooded heritage, and their relative frailty, they are highly "
"valued as scouts as they can navigate through rough terrain and around "
"opponents. The best Skirmishers go on to become Saurian Ambushers."
msgstr ""
"蜥蜴人刺客善于用矛作武器。尽管他们天生冷血，也有他们亲戚的弱点。他们很适合作"
"为侦察兵，正如他们有着粗糙地形上的优势。他们拥有这些事实上的优势。最好的蜥蜴"
"人刺客会成为蜥蜴人伏兵。"

#: data/units/Saurian_Soothsayer.cfg:4
msgid "Saurian Soothsayer"
msgstr "蜥蜴人占卜师"

#: data/units/Saurian_Soothsayer.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Saurian Soothsayers are highly valued as healers because they can provide "
"aid to their friends regardless of terrain or opposition. In addition to "
"curing their allies they possess knowledge of cold magic."
msgstr ""
"蜥蜴人占卜师有着和治疗者一样高的价值，因为他们能支援盟军而无论地形或位置。除"
"了能治愈盟军之外，他们也会冰冻魔法。"

#: data/units/Saurian_Tribalist.cfg:4
msgid "Saurian Tribalist"
msgstr "蜥蜴人投石手"

#: data/units/Saurian_Tribalist.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Despite their lethargic cold blooded heritage, and their relative frailty, "
"Saurian Tribalists are valued as healers because they can provide aid to "
"their allies regardless of terrain or opposition. In addition to healing "
"they possess knowledge of cold magic."
msgstr ""
"尽管他们天生冷血，也有他们亲戚的弱点。蜥蜴人投石手有着和治疗者一样高的价值，"
"因为他们能支援盟军而无论地形或位置。除了能治愈盟军之外，他们也会冰冻魔法。"

#: data/units/Sea_Serpent.cfg:3
msgid "Sea Serpent"
msgstr "海洋巨蛇"

#: data/units/Sea_Serpent.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Sea Serpents are gigantic monsters, capable of capsizing boats by themselves."
msgstr "海洋巨蛇是巨大的怪兽，有着颠覆船只的能力。"

#: data/units/Sergeant.cfg:3
msgid "Sergeant"
msgstr "军士"

#: data/units/Sergeant.cfg:29
msgid ""
"The Sergeant is an officer in the ranks of the Royal Army. Though "
"academically trained, he will need some experience in the field before his "
"leadership is sound and acknowledged."
msgstr ""
"军士是皇家卫队的教官。虽然受到学院式训练，在有着公认的领导技能之前需要更多的"
"战斗经验。"

#: data/units/Shadow.cfg:3
msgid "Shadow"
msgstr "影者"

#: data/units/Shadow.cfg:29
msgid ""
"When light came into the world and gave form to the unknown, fear was forced "
"to retreat into darkness. Since that day, the shadows of the world have held "
"terror for humanity, though it knows not why.\n"
"\n"
"That is a question which is easily answered by a necromancer.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: while a unit with the same allegiance as the shadow distracts "
"an enemy, the shadow may strike at the opponent's back, inflicting double "
"damage. Shadows have very unusual resistances to damage, and move quite "
"slowly over open water. Shadows are able to hide at night, leaving no trace "
"of their presence."
msgstr ""
"当光明降于人世并给予未事物以形态，恐惧被迫退至阴影里。至那之后世界的阴影就成"
"为人类恐惧的源泉，尽管不知原因。\n"
"\n"
"这是个让死灵法师很容易回答的问题。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：当一个单位把影者盟友作为敌人时，他们会对敌人进行背刺，造成双倍伤"
"害。他们对伤害有着非凡的抗性，在水面上移动很慢。影者能在夜幕下隐藏行踪，不留"
"下任何痕迹。"

#: data/units/Shock_Trooper.cfg:3
msgid "Shock Trooper"
msgstr "突击骑兵"

#: data/units/Shock_Trooper.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Shock troopers are the elite of the heavy infantry, and half of their use in "
"war is simply a matter of intimidation. The only men who can enter their "
"ranks are prodigiously well-built, and when clad in black plate brimming "
"with spikes, they are a fearsome sight to behold. The sight of Shock "
"Troopers breaking an enemy with their morning stars is often enough to "
"shatter the morale of any opposition, who sometimes wonder if such armor "
"covers monsters, rather than men. The drawback of such heavy armor is, of "
"course, the time it takes to move into and out of combat."
msgstr ""
"突击骑兵是重甲步兵中的精英，半数的他们运用于战斗是很恐怖的事。仅仅能达到这个"
"等级的人异常强的兵种，当他们穿着黑色钉刺板甲，那种威严的气势是很恐怖的。他们"
"的标志攻击是晨星攻击，通常能粉碎敌人的信心，有时被惊异的认为是裹着装甲的怪物"
"而非人。穿着重甲的缺点是需要点时间才能移动到战斗所需的位置。"

#: data/units/Silver_Mage.cfg:3
msgid "Silver Mage"
msgstr "银魔法师"

#: data/units/Silver_Mage.cfg:30
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The many paths that a mage can take in study lead to strikingly different "
"ends. Silver magi have devoted themselves to a study of the forces that bind "
"reality together, and have managed, somewhat, to unravel the mysteries of a "
"world far more vast than most would ever imagine. Often viewed as sages, or "
"wandering mystics, silver magi act under an agenda which is obscure even to "
"their own colleagues. Though helpful to the magisteriums which often employ "
"them in the field, they remain somewhat aloof.\n"
"\n"
"They have, in fact, their own order amongst the ranks of magi, an order "
"which withholds certain secrets from their peers. One of these is an "
"apparent ability to cross great distances, faster than one could possibly "
"travel on foot. Members of the silver order ardently refuse to discuss the "
"workings of this with any of their fellow magi, and on those rare occasions "
"when others have pried into their work, they have abandoned the endeavor, "
"never to speak of it again.\n"
"\n"
"Silver magi are often more physically adept than other magi, and their "
"skills are of undeniable use on the battlefield, if one can manage to coerce "
"the mage into applying them.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the ranged attack of a silver mage is magical, and always has "
"a high chance of hitting an opponent. Silver Magi are well-attuned to their "
"magical natures and are highly resistant to non-physical damage. They can "
"also teleport between any two villages instantly, though the player must "
"control both, and the destination village must be unoccupied."
msgstr ""
"成为魔法师的不同之路会造成不同的学习效果。最终，银魔法师学习到利用和控制物体"
"的力量。某些事物，是解开那些难以想象的世界之谜关键。通常被认为是圣人，或徘徊"
"的神秘者，银魔法师常常默默无闻的工作。虽然受雇佣于战场之上起教诲作用，但他们"
"却有几分超然于世。\n"
"\n"
"事实上，他们有着他们自己等级的魔法力量，对他们的同伴来说很是神秘。其中一个是"
"能在极短的时间内，能比那些最快步兵到达更远的地方。当别人介入时，这些法师的成"
"员非常避讳于别人讨论他们工作的方式，如果无须，他们将不会再谈起。\n"
"\n"
"银魔法师通常被认为事实上强于其他法师，他们在战场上的能力是不容置疑的，如果有"
"人能强制他们加入的话。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：他们的远程攻击是魔法攻击，并对敌人有很高的击中比率。他们对很多形式"
"的魔法攻击有很高的抗性。他们也能在任意两个村庄之间传送，然而玩家必须有这两个"
"村庄的控制权。"

#: data/units/Silver_Mage.cfg:152
msgid "female^Silver Mage"
msgstr "女性银魔法师"

#: data/units/Skeleton.cfg:3
msgid "Skeleton"
msgstr "骷髅人"

#: data/units/Skeleton.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Skeletons are warriors who have been slain in battle and brought back by "
"dark magics. Nearly mindless, and unwavering in their purpose, they fear "
"neither pain, nor death, and their mere presence will often frighten away "
"any who would challenge their master."
msgstr ""
"骷髅人是曾经骁勇善战的战士，死后被黑暗魔法召回回来。差不多没有心智，并有坚定"
"的目标，他们感觉不到痛苦或死亡，他们会把那些企图挑战他们主人的生物作为敌人，"
"而去战斗。"

#: data/units/Skeleton_Archer.cfg:3
msgid "Skeleton Archer"
msgstr "骷髅弓箭手"

#: data/units/Skeleton_Archer.cfg:24
msgid ""
"A skeleton archer is little different from the 'skeletons' which often "
"accompany it - it is a sin against nature, a warrior raised from the dead to "
"fight once again. In their master's hands, these soldiers will do anything "
"to achieve the tasks laid before them, for death holds no fear for one who "
"is already dead."
msgstr ""
"骷髅弓箭手和‘骷髅人’有点不同且常常作为他们的补充 － 这是大自然的罪过，死后重"
"新召回并继续战斗。掌握在他们主人的手中，这些战士能作任何给予的人物，对于死"
"亡，一个已死的人是不会害怕的。"

#: data/units/Soul_Shooter.cfg:3
msgid "Soul Shooter"
msgstr "灵魂射手"

#: data/units/Soul_Shooter.cfg:35
msgid ""
"The most powerful of the undead archers invariably end up being those who "
"were themselves archers in their previous life. They wander the fields of "
"battle, guided by the fading memory of their former skill, neither knowing, "
"nor caring what their purpose, or foes be. They are driven only by a malice "
"borne of the anguish of their empty and incoherent existence."
msgstr ""
"许多强力的不死弓箭手被召回后继续这他们生前所从事的职业。他们徘徊于战场，被以"
"渐渐消去的生前战斗形式所引导，没有心智，且没有目标或敌人。他们仅仅带着对他们"
"空虚存在怨恨而存在。"

#: data/units/Soulless.cfg:5
msgid "Soulless"
msgstr "无魂怪"

#: data/units/Soulless.cfg:28
msgid ""
"These animated walking corpses have become strong from long experience "
"fighting the living."
msgstr "这些行尸走肉由生前充足的战斗经验而变得强壮。"

#: data/units/Spearman.cfg:3
msgid "Spearman"
msgstr "矛兵"

#: data/units/Spearman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Swords are, for many, an expensive luxury, and one which peasants can ill "
"afford. Spears are much easier to make and will do well even without a head, "
"though most can afford one. Clad in leather armor, and often armed with a "
"shield and a few javelins, spearmen are the staple of most armies, often "
"thrown into the front lines with only basic training.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the length of their weapon allows a spearman to strike first "
"in melee, even in defense."
msgstr ""
"剑，对于许多人来说是奢侈的武器，是那些农夫买不起的。矛则能轻易制作并容易操"
"控，而且很多人都买的起。装备皮甲，并常常装备盾牌和少量的标枪，矛兵是许多军队"
"的主要构成，常常不经训练就投入前线。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：长长的武器使得他们有先攻权，即使是在防御中。"

#: data/units/Spectre.cfg:3
msgid "Spectre"
msgstr "妖怪"

#: data/units/Spectre.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Sometimes called the 'hollow men', spectres form the right arm of their "
"master's power. These abominations are a rightful terror to the living, and "
"keep a sleepless vigil over their master's domain.\n"
"\n"
"The creation of these is no mean feat; the real danger in encountering one "
"is that it is likely only the harbinger of a much more dangerous force that "
"will follow in its wake.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: a strike from their blade will drain life from the victim, to "
"renew the spectre. Spectres have very unusual resistances to damage, and "
"move quite slowly over open water."
msgstr ""
"有时被称为‘窟窿人’，妖怪是他们主人力量的表现形式。这些令人厌恶的生物在生者眼"
"中是可怕的，并在他们主人的领地上不眠不休的监视着。\n"
"\n"
"创造这些生物并不意味着壮举：正真的危险是当他们醒来之后未知的危险力量。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：他们的剑刃攻击会吸血，并治疗自己。他们对伤害有非凡的抗性，在水面上"
"移动很慢。"

#: data/units/Swordsman.cfg:3
msgid "Swordsman"
msgstr "剑士"

#: data/units/Swordsman.cfg:27
msgid ""
"An experienced soldier will often save enough to equip a suit of scale or "
"chain armor, and a sturdy broadsword. Though trading their spears for swords "
"is often a somewhat jarring change, most spearmen will leap at the chance, "
"knowing all too well the limitations of the weapon they are leaving behind. "
"A sword is not without its own drawbacks, but is much more maneuverable than "
"a spear, and much better in close quarters."
msgstr ""
"经验充足的战士通常能装备套装或链甲，和强健的大刀。虽然训练他们剑刺，常常会有"
"不和谐的改变，许多矛兵会有机会改变，据知他们能很好的了解留在后面武器的缺陷。"
"剑也有缺陷，但却比矛有更多的机动性，并在狭小的空间更好用。"

#: data/units/Tentacle.cfg:3
msgid "Tentacle of the Deep"
msgstr "深渊触手"

#: data/units/Tentacle.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Tentacles of the Deep are the appendages of some larger monster that lurks "
"below the waves."
msgstr "深渊触手常常属于那些隐藏在海浪以下的巨大怪物。"

#: data/units/Thief.cfg:3
msgid "Thief"
msgstr "小偷"

#: data/units/Thief.cfg:18
msgid ""
"For as long as anyone can remember, the members of the various 'guilds' of "
"rat-catchers that spring up in any larger city have had a curious practice "
"of bleaching their hair with lime till it becomes a pale shade of blue. It "
"is a bold thing to do, as their profession often delves into less-than-legal "
"enterprises. Thieves have many skills, and by necessity are both light on "
"their feet, and good with knives. They happily employ less-than-honorable "
"tactics in combat, seeing little purpose in a 'fair fight'.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: while a unit with the same allegiance as the thief distracts "
"an enemy, the thief may backstab, inflicting double damage, by creeping "
"around behind that enemy."
msgstr ""
"只要任何人能记起，出现在许多大都市里的不同捕鼠者‘团体’的成员，有着古怪的行为"
"把他们的头发漂白成苍蓝色。这是一个大胆的事，他们常常从事非法业务。小偷有许多"
"技能，必有的两项是轻轻的脚步和良好的小刀技能。他们乐于使用阴险的战术，不屑"
"于‘公平战斗’。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：当敌人把小偷的盟友作为攻击目标是，他们能绕到敌人背后，进行背刺，造"
"成双倍伤害。"

#: data/units/Thief.cfg:106
msgid "female^Thief"
msgstr "女性小偷"

#: data/units/Thug.cfg:3
msgid "Thug"
msgstr "暴徒"

#: data/units/Thug.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Thugs come from a wide variety of sources; while a few are born into "
"thuggery, many are former soldiers deemed unfit to serve in the army or "
"peasants thrown off their lands. They quickly become thugs as a means of "
"sustenance. Regardless of their background, they all share the practice of "
"beating their victims with large clubs."
msgstr ""
"暴徒来源于多种形式：一些是天生的暴徒，许多是那些不适合服务的士兵或丢掉田地的"
"农夫。他们为了活命而快速成为暴徒。无论他们的背景。他们都善于用大木棒进行攻"
"击。"

#: data/units/Transport_Galleon.cfg:3
msgid "Transport Galleon"
msgstr "运输大帆船"

#: data/units/Transport_Galleon.cfg:15
msgid ""
"Transport Galleons are well-armed ships that carry troops. If they reach the "
"shore, they can deposit the troops to attack."
msgstr ""
"运输大帆船大多护卫良好而用来运送部队。一旦到达海岸，就能放下所装载的部队去战"
"斗。"

#: data/units/Trapper.cfg:3
msgid "Trapper"
msgstr "设陷井者"

#: data/units/Trapper.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Trappers usually work supplying food for bandits and outlaws. Their hunting "
"experience makes them most valuable at night and in forests and swamps."
msgstr ""
"他们常常为罪犯和强盗提供事物。他们守猎的经验帮助他们在夜晚很有价值，在森林这"
"沼泽也是。"

#: data/units/Troll.cfg:3
msgid "Troll"
msgstr "巨魔"

#: data/units/Troll.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Trolls have been a mote to trouble the thoughts of humanity and dwarf-kind, "
"who remain baffled at the origins of these creatures, and perhaps more "
"importantly, the driving force behind their unnatural vitality and strength. "
"A fully-grown troll towers above a man, and, even unarmed, would be a great "
"threat in combat. The large clubs typically favored in fighting act as "
"extensions of their arms, used for the same purpose of mauling their prey "
"into submission.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Trolls possess the regeneration ability, which heals them as "
"though they were always stationed in a village."
msgstr ""
"巨魔是人类和矮人们微小的麻烦，他们困惑于自己的起源，可能更重要的是，他们背后"
"操作的非自然生命和力量。完全成长的巨魔身高高于人类，即使没有武装，在战斗中也"
"是一个威胁。他们部队通常使用大木棒进行攻击，他们也使用大槌进行同样的目的。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：巨魔拥有重生能力，就想呆在村庄那样治疗他们。"

#: data/units/Troll_Hero.cfg:3
msgid "Troll Hero"
msgstr "巨魔英雄"

#: data/units/Troll_Hero.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Some trolls are born with an undue share of the strength and vitality that "
"characterizes their race. In a society where might makes right, those of "
"their ilk revere them as heroes.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Trolls possess the regeneration ability, which heals them as "
"though they were always stationed in a village."
msgstr ""
"一些巨魔天生神力和强大的生命。在他们所生活的社会中，同族人称他们为英雄。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：巨魔拥有重生能力，就想呆在村庄那样治疗他们。"

#: data/units/Troll_Rocklobber.cfg:3
msgid "Troll Rocklobber"
msgstr "巨魔巨石投手"

#: data/units/Troll_Rocklobber.cfg:29
msgid ""
"The thought of throwing a boulder in combat has certainly occurred to many "
"trolls, and some have taken to them as a weapon of choice. Because such "
"stones are not always easy to find, Rocklobbers have taken to carrying them "
"in sacks slung over their shoulders. The same leather out of which the sack "
"is formed is easily adapted to a crude sling.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: though unwieldy, a stone thrown by one of these monsters is "
"much more deadly than any arrow, if it manages to hit. Trolls possess the "
"regeneration ability, which heals them as though they were always stationed "
"in a village."
msgstr ""
"投掷石头的战术是许多巨魔所用到的，有些则选择这作为主要武器。因为这些石头不是"
"很好找，巨石投石手把它们装到大袋里扛在身上。和麻布袋同样形式的皮袋也用于装载"
"这些石头。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：尽管笨拙，一个投掷出的巨石却是比任何箭更致命的，如果刚好击中的话。"
"巨魔拥有重生能力，就想呆在村庄那样治疗他们。"

#: data/units/Troll_Warrior.cfg:3
msgid "Troll Warrior"
msgstr "巨魔勇士"

#: data/units/Troll_Warrior.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Trolls typically neither need nor prefer to use any proper armament in "
"combat, as large 'sticks and stones' serve them all too well. However, "
"trolls have been seen on numerous occasions clad in rough-shod armor and "
"bearing metal hammers. It is speculated that their typical orcish allies are "
"the source and often crafters of these, as expeditions into several forcibly-"
"vacated troll holes have shown little evidence of tool use, and certainly no "
"metalworking of any kind. Given how dangerous a troll is in combat, the "
"thought of a troll in full armor is entirely unsettling.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Trolls possess the regeneration ability, which heals them as "
"though they were always stationed in a village."
msgstr ""
"巨魔根本不需要或喜欢用任何金属装备，大‘木棒和石头’更适合他们。然而，巨魔在很"
"多场合被见到装备粗糙的金属鞋和金属锤。可能他们的兽人盟友给他们提供这些装备，"
"因为他们没有使用金属制造物品的技术。有巨魔的战斗是危险的，更不用说装备全身装"
"备的巨魔。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：巨魔拥有重生能力，就想呆在村庄那样治疗他们。"

#: data/units/Troll_Whelp.cfg:3
msgid "Troll Whelp"
msgstr "巨魔小崽"

#: data/units/Troll_Whelp.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Describing a troll as a whelp is something of an oxymoron, given that their "
"bodies are already much hardier than that of a grown man. They are clumsy "
"and not yet capable of walking properly, forced instead to shamble about on "
"all fours, but any inhibition this causes them is more than made up for by "
"the raw strength of their race.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Trolls possess the regeneration ability, which heals them as "
"though they were always stationed in a village."
msgstr ""
"描述巨魔是小崽有时是矛盾的。他们的身体常常强于成年人。他们笨拙并不能很好的行"
"走，有时用四肢来蹒跚行走，但这些不便并不影响他们有着和同族人同样的力量。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：巨魔拥有重生能力，就想呆在村庄那样治疗他们。"

#: data/units/Vampire_Bat.cfg:3
msgid "Vampire Bat"
msgstr "吸血蝙蝠"

#: data/units/Vampire_Bat.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Vampire Bats are undead flying beasts that attack by biting their victims. "
"While their fangs are not very powerful, the health of victims is drained "
"away along with their blood, and given to the Bats."
msgstr ""
"吸血蝙蝠是不死飞行兽，并用咬来进行攻击。虽然他们的牙并不太强力，受害者的血液"
"会被吸干，并治疗自己。"

#: data/units/Walking_Corpse.cfg:5
msgid "Walking Corpse"
msgstr "僵尸"

#: data/units/Walking_Corpse.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Walking Corpses are the bodies of the dead, re-animated by dark magic. "
"Although weak in combat, these zombies can spread their curse to those they "
"kill, increasing the army of undead."
msgstr ""
"僵尸是死去人们的躯壳，被黑暗魔法召回回来。虽然疏于战斗，这些僵尸会诅咒那些被"
"杀死的敌人，召回他们加入不死军队。"

#: data/units/Walking_Corpse.cfg:56
msgid "plague"
msgstr "瘟疫"

#: data/units/White_Mage.cfg:3
msgid "White Mage"
msgstr "白魔法师"

#: data/units/White_Mage.cfg:38
msgid ""
"Some magi, as they learn about the world around them, and learn the truth of "
"the suffering and squalor in which humanity too often lives, find that they "
"cannot bring themselves to be cloistered into a life of study. These men and "
"women give up the life of a mage, and join monastic orders, dedicating the "
"skills they have been given to the good of all. After their ordination, they "
"often travel the world, ministering to sickness and injury.\n"
"\n"
"Though not trained for combat, there is one enemy against which they are a "
"potent ally. If need arises, they can call on the power of the Light to "
"banish the unworldly from the mortal plane.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: the light cast by a white mage is magical in nature, and "
"always has a high chance of hitting an opponent. This light does tremendous "
"damage to the undead, and can even damage living creatures. White magi are "
"capable of healing units around them, and curing them of poison."
msgstr ""
"许多魔法师，通过学习周围的世界和学习痛苦的真谛，和人类生命中的贫苦，发现那些"
"不能使他们紧闭一生去学习的地方。这人人和女人放弃魔法生命，而加入修道院神职人"
"员，献出他们所学习到的所有技能用于公益事业。当被任命后，他们常常环游世界，治"
"疗疾病和伤害。\n"
"\n"
"虽然不善于作战，他们却是一种敌人天生的对手：如果军事需要，他们能召唤光明的力"
"量来驱散一切不属于人世间的非正常生物形式。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：他们所召唤的光明力量是自然魔法攻击，并对敌人有很高的击中比率。这力"
"量能对不死造成巨大的伤害，即使对有些生物也是。白魔法师能治疗相邻的友好单位，"
"并治愈中毒。"

#: data/units/White_Mage.cfg:115
msgid "female^White Mage"
msgstr "女性白魔法师"

#: data/units/Wolf_Rider.cfg:3
msgid "Wolf Rider"
msgstr "狼骑兵"

#: data/units/Wolf_Rider.cfg:66
msgid ""
"No one is quite sure how the practice of taming and riding wolves came into "
"being. Goblins are smaller and much weaker than orcs. Any who can manage to "
"win themselves a mount have a much safer, and daresay, more amusing role in "
"combat.\n"
"\n"
"Wolves, likely, could never support the weight of a man in plate, but a "
"goblin in leather armor is a simple load to bear. Quite unlike horses, these "
"mounts have a rather easy time traversing the mountains, though water and "
"woods will still slow them down."
msgstr ""
"没人能确定什么时候开始训练狼作为坐骑。地精比兽人小和虚弱。能搭载他们能会使他"
"们更安全，我想，会有更多有趣的事情在战斗中发生。\n"
"\n"
"狼永远不能承受一个人的重量，但是穿作皮甲的地精就要容易的多。完全不像马，这些"
"狼能在山脉上迅速的穿行，尽管水和森林会减慢他们的速度。"

#: data/units/Wose.cfg:3
msgid "Wose"
msgstr "树人"

#: data/units/Wose.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Rarely seen, even by elves, a Wose is an order of creature about which "
"little is known. The elves are the source of most of this knowledge; they "
"know that these beings are not descended from trees, despite the similarity "
"in form, and they know that a wose is more closely tied to the faerie world "
"than the elves themselves, though in a different way. The motives and "
"workings of their kind are unknown, though most posit the obvious idea that "
"woses are wardens of the natural world.\n"
"\n"
"Woses are utterly unwarlike, but possess a great strength. They are, "
"however, neither used to, nor quick at moving around.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: Woses regenerate by using natural resources around them, "
"without needing to huddle in villages to obtain sustenance and aid."
msgstr ""
"极少见，即使对精灵来说也一样，树人是极少非正常的生命形式。精灵是这些认知的发"
"源地：他们知道这些生物不是由树生成，尽管有着相同的形式，并且他们知道树人比精"
"灵更接近仙境世界，虽然是以不同的方式。他们的动机和运行方式还不可知，尽管大多"
"数意见认为他们是自然世界的保护者。\n"
"\n"
"他们不好战，但拥有强大的力量。然而他们不善于迅速的移动。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：树人使用周围的自然力量来重生，而不需要呆在村庄等待支援或帮助。"

#: data/units/Wraith.cfg:3
msgid "Wraith"
msgstr "幻影"

#: data/units/Wraith.cfg:26
msgid ""
"These tortured forms of what were once warriors are among the most "
"terrifying things a necromancer can create, for a sword will cleave right "
"through them, as through air itself. What inspires such fear is the thought "
"that these beasts are invincible, a belief that is actually far from the "
"truth.\n"
"\n"
"Because of this, a means was made by which the enchantments that drive these "
"creatures could renew themselves through the very thing which threatened "
"them.\n"
"\n"
"Special Notes: a strike from their blade will drain life from the victim, to "
"renew the wraith. Wraiths have very unusual resistances to damage, and move "
"quite slowly over open water."
msgstr ""
"这些曾经的勇士被死灵法师召唤出来，而形成糟糕扭曲的生命形式，一把剑就能轻易的"
"穿过他们，因为他们就是空气。这些生物不惧怕死亡，使得他们有点无敌，一个信念竟"
"这样远离真像。\n"
"\n"
"因为这样，召唤他们出来的妖术能恢复他们。\n"
"\n"
"特别提示：他们的剑攻击能吸血，并治疗自己。幻影有非凡的伤害抗性，在水里会减慢"
"移动速度。"

#: data/units/Yeti.cfg:3
msgid "Yeti"
msgstr "雪人"

#: data/units/Yeti.cfg:37
msgid ""
"Little is known about Yetis, ape-like creatures said to live in remote and "
"snow-covered mountains. Few profess to have seen one, and their existence is "
"doubted by many."
msgstr ""
"雪人是未知的，这些生物生活在偏僻的白雪覆盖的山脉里。极少能见到一个，他们的存"
"在一直受到人们的质疑。"

#: data/units/Young_Ogre.cfg:3
msgid "Young Ogre"
msgstr "年轻食人魔"

#: data/units/Young_Ogre.cfg:22
msgid ""
"When still young, Ogres are sometimes captured and taken into the army to be "
"trained. They cannot manage weapons skillfully, but that is of little "
"concern given their strength."
msgstr ""
"虽然仍然年轻，他们有时也被投入军队中而被受训。他们并不能熟练的使用武器，但却"
"不用担心他们的强大力量。"

